Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.28,0:00:07.40,注人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(798,404)}西绪弗斯公司出品
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.67,0:00:27.90,歌词,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1102,266)} 是时候逃离
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.06,0:00:27.90,歌词,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1102,316)}生死存亡的关头
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.75,0:00:27.90,歌词,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1094,366)}不 这不是游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.65,0:00:27.90,歌词,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1088,416)}只是新的开始
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.29,0:00:46.67,注人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(310,556)}珊农·莱托
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.70,0:00:46.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这张专辑是关于\N{\fs30}This record is about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.68,0:00:48.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,克服挑战的\N{\fs30}overcoming challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.70,0:00:50.85,Artifact,,0,0,0,,为自己坚信的事情而斗争\N{\fs30}It's very important to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:53.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是很重要的\N{\fs30}fight for what you feel is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.84,0:00:53.81,注人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(432,556)}托莫·米利舍维奇
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.51,0:00:59.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们被逼进了死角\N{\fs30}We were backed into a corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.80,0:01:02.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,对我们来说 不成功 便成仁\N{\fs30}For us, it was all or nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.80,0:01:04.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,有时候我们必须\N{\fs30}Sometimes you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.40,0:01:07.15,注人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(354,562)}杰瑞德·莱托
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.22,0:01:06.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,为自由而战\N{\fs30}fight in order to be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.40,0:01:12.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,<全面开战>这张专辑\N{\fs30}"This Is War" is an album
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.02,0:01:14.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是关于斗争的\N{\fs30}about conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.28,0:01:15.71,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们迎来了一场大战\N{\fs30}We had a huge battle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.71,0:01:16.79,Artifact,,0,0,0,,对方是我们的唱片公司\N{\fs30}with our record company.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.00,0:01:18.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这张专辑就纪录了\N{\fs30}The album kind of documented
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.41,0:01:19.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们生命中\N{\fs30}this really turbulent time
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.99,0:01:20.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这个混乱的时期\N{\fs30}in our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.00,0:01:24.95,Artifact,,0,0,0,,唱片公司与艺人之间\N{\fs30}There has always been a serious
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.42,0:01:27.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,总是有这么一种相当严重的\N{\fs30}distrust between an artist
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.86,0:01:29.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不信任关系\N{\fs30}and their record label.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.80,0:01:30.85,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我从没听过有哪家唱片公司\N{\fs30}I never heard of a label
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.85,0:01:31.92,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是不坑艺人的\N{\fs30}that doesn't screw an artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.92,0:01:33.24,Artifact,,0,0,0,,商业模式就是这样\N{\fs30}That's the business model
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.48,0:01:34.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,靠坑艺人来赚钱\N{\fs30}is screwing the artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.27,0:01:38.56,Artifact,,0,0,0,,乐队里谁也没想过\N{\fs30}None of us in a band ever dreamed
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.56,0:01:40.41,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们会如此幸运\N{\fs30}that we would be so lucky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.03,0:01:42.41,注人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(526,514)}巴塞洛缪·卡宾斯 导演
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.41,0:01:42.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,能取得这样的成功\N{\fs30}to have the success that we've had.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.40,0:01:46.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但现在\N{\fs30}Now here we were faced
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.30,0:01:47.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们所拥有的一切\N{\fs30}with the possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.44,0:01:48.35,Artifact,,0,0,0,,又都面临着\N{\fs30}that everything was gonna be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.35,0:01:50.53,Artifact,,0,0,0,,即将被剥夺的境地\N{\fs30}ripped right away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.73,0:02:11.44,地名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(626,406)}3年前
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.60,0:02:13.22,Artifact,,0,0,0,,全面的经济风暴\N{\fs30}There is a kind of economic
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.22,0:02:14.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,正在酝酿\N{\fs30}perfect storm brewing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.10,0:02:16.13,Artifact,,0,0,0,,情况很糟糕\N{\fs30}disastrous situation
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.60,0:02:17.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们快要失去工作!\N{\fs30}they're losing their jobs
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.94,0:02:19.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,油价上升\N{\fs30}rising gas prices
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.29,0:02:22.17,Artifact,,0,0,0,,朋友们 美国同胞们\N{\fs30}My friends and fellow Americans,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.65,0:02:25.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我很高兴\N{\fs30}I am very pleased and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.88,0:02:27.85,Artifact,,0,0,0,,也很荣幸地 向你们介绍\N{\fs30}very privileged to introduce to you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.50,0:02:30.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,下一位美国副总统\N{\fs30}the next vice-president of the United States:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.00,0:02:43.27,Artifact,,0,0,0,,萨拉·佩林州长\N{\fs30}Governor Sarah Palin
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.75,0:02:45.53,Artifact,,0,0,0,,来自杰出的阿拉斯加州!\N{\fs30}of the great state of Alaska.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.87,0:02:54.39,地名,,0,0,0,,洛杉矶
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.70,0:03:04.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,军号嘹亮\N{\fs30}You can hear the bugles blaring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.90,0:03:07.31,Artifact,,0,0,0,,羌管悠悠\N{\fs30}The sound of the battle cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.70,0:03:10.01,Artifact,,0,0,0,,战鼓擂擂\N{\fs30}The march of the drum
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.70,0:03:12.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,惊醒吾眠\N{\fs30}calling me from my slumber,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.30,0:03:17.00,Artifact,,0,0,0,,起身赶赴\N{\fs30}pushing me toward
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.50,0:03:21.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,朝阳 战场\N{\fs30}A new day. A new fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.32,0:03:26.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,噢 哇.. 噢 哇...\N{\fs30}Oh wow... Oh wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.55,0:03:31.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,太他妈亮\N{\fs30}It's too fucking bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.50,0:03:46.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,JL:这是2008年\N{\fs30}It was 2008, we were on the road
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.59,0:03:48.66,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们已经巡演了2年\N{\fs30}for over 2 years and had recently
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.90,0:03:50.21,Artifact,,0,0,0,,刚刚回到洛杉矶\N{\fs30}returned to Los Angeles to work
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:51.45,Artifact,,0,0,0,,来制作我们的第三张专辑\N{\fs30}on our third album.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.85,0:03:55.17,Artifact,,0,0,0,,摸爬滚打了10年\N{\fs30}After over a decade of struggling,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.17,0:03:56.45,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们终于有了点突破\N{\fs30}we finally had a breakthrough
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.45,0:03:57.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,取得了些成就\N{\fs30}and achieved more success
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.55,0:03:59.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这是我们想都不敢想的\N{\fs30}than we ever dreamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.30,0:04:01.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们的第二张专辑<美丽的谎言>\N{\fs30}Our second album A Beautiful Lie
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.10,0:04:03.95,Artifact,,0,0,0,,售出了超过350万张\N{\fs30}sold over 3,5 Million copies
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.56,0:04:07.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们也因此有机会进行全球巡演\N{\fs30}and gave us the chance to tour the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.72,0:04:09.35,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们都为人生的这段历程\N{\fs30}We were all incredibly excited
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.35,0:04:10.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,激动不已\N{\fs30}about this time in our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.31,0:04:12.98,Artifact,,0,0,0,,于是决定把新专辑的制作过程\N{\fs30}and we decided to make a film
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.98,0:04:14.41,Artifact,,0,0,0,,拍成一部电影  然而...\N{\fs30}about the next album but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.60,0:04:18.15,Artifact,,0,0,0,,突然一切都变了味\N{\fs30}It quickly turned into something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.43,0:04:23.87,Artifact,,0,0,0,,30秒上火星被起诉赔偿...\N{\fs30}Thirty Seconds to Mars is being sued for...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.87,0:04:26.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,3000万美元！挺萌的吧\N{\fs30}30 Million Dollars! Cute! Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:28.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,今夏 该乐队的唱片公司 维京/百代EMI\N{\fs30}This summer, the band's label Virgin/EMI
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.63,0:04:30.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,以违约之名\N{\fs30}filed a breach-of-contract suit
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.46,0:04:31.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,起诉了30秒上火星\N{\fs30}against Thirty Seconds to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.05,0:04:33.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而Jared却坚称\N{\fs30}However, Jared insists
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.14,0:04:35.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,乐队只是在行使其合法权利\N{\fs30}that the band was just exercising their legal rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.41,0:04:41.36,网页,,0,0,0,,{\b0\pos(454,406)}莱托在乐队网站上回应{\c&H1111DB&}违约{\c&H000001&}诉讼
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.70,0:04:42.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们要啥？\N{\fs30}What do they want?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.65,0:04:43.79,Artifact,,0,0,0,,三千万美元\N{\fs30}30 Million Dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.57,0:04:47.51,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(66,698)}电台DJ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.05,0:04:50.35,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(716,636)}"我们卖了200多万张\N专辑却没拿到一分钱\N 是不是难以置信..."—JL
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.15,0:04:47.92,Artifact,,0,0,0,,真的咩?\N{\fs30}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.13,0:04:53.66,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你被要求赔偿 三千 万 美元！\N{\fs30}You're being sued for 30 Million Dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.34,0:04:57.35,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(66,588)}前EMI传媒创意服务部 副部长
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.29,0:04:56.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这你...呃...\N{\fs30}What are you?... Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.19,0:04:57.37,Artifact,,0,0,0,,晚上怎么睡得着觉呢\N{\fs30}How do you sleep at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.95,0:05:00.63,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我不知道这个数字是怎么来的\N{\fs30}I have no idea where the number came from
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.35,0:05:02.15,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(366,588)}维京/百代要求30秒上火星\N赔偿$3000万 莱托回击
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.83,0:05:01.72,Artifact,,0,0,0,,除了...\N{\fs30}other than...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.53,0:05:06.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这肯定不是为了媒体炒作而瞎说出来的\N{\fs30}It certainly wasn't a wink to the press or
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.22,0:05:07.72,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(970,588)}前EMI首席财务官
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.24,0:05:07.93,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不然也不会用这个数字\N{\fs30}were we clever to use the same number...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.76,0:05:10.33,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(524,414)}百代唱片(EMI)找到了盈利新方式：
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.40,0:05:12.93,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(472,450)}起诉自家艺人.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.93,0:05:16.70,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(64,552)}三十秒上火星乐队 律师
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.65,0:05:14.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,30STM的专辑十分热销\N{\fs30}Thirty Seconds to Mars have just sold a lot of...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:16.92,Artifact,,0,0,0,,卖的很好 但他们却没赚到钱\N{\fs30}a lot of albums and never made any money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.92,0:05:18.52,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们也没想着赚什么大钱\N{\fs30}We weren't really expecting a bunch of money
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.02,0:05:21.86,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(74,554)}三十秒上火星乐队 主唱
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.45,0:05:21.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们只是觉得奇怪\N{\fs30}we just thought it bizarre that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.19,0:05:25.92,Artifact,,0,0,0,,专辑得到了这么大的收益\N{\fs30}that all this revenue was being generated
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.92,0:05:30.63,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但我们却仍然负债270万美元\N{\fs30}and that we were still 2.7 Million Dollars in debt so,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.63,0:05:32.95,Artifact,,0,0,0,,于是我们进行了调查\N{\fs30}we started to look into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.62,0:05:37.46,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(74,554)}三十秒上火星乐队 经理人
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.95,0:05:34.11,Artifact,,0,0,0,,30STM的合同\N{\fs30}30STM suffered a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.11,0:05:36.51,Artifact,,0,0,0,,甚至并不是\N{\fs30}contract that really wasn't even
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.51,0:05:37.67,Artifact,,0,0,0,,直接与EMI签的\N{\fs30}a direct contract with EMI,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.80,0:05:38.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这是个垃圾协议\N{\fs30}it was bad deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.31,0:05:40.76,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们说的意思 就是让我们闭嘴\N{\fs30}They basically told us to shut up
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.76,0:05:42.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,赶紧去做下一张专辑\N{\fs30}and go make another album.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.05,0:05:47.89,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(894,554)}三十秒上火星乐队 鼓手
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.39,0:05:45.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们没有回应\N{\fs30}They weren't addressing our concerns
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.03,0:05:46.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们对于合约的质疑\N{\fs30}that we had with the contracts,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.32,0:05:48.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所以我们决定终止跟EMI的合同\N{\fs30}so we decided to terminate with EMI.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.86,0:05:51.92,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们签了9年\N{\fs30}We've been signed for 9 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.27,0:05:54.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但根据加州法律\N{\fs30}Under California law, you can't be held
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.24,0:05:55.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,超过7年你就可以单方面解约\N{\fs30}bound to a contract for more than 7 years
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.40,0:05:58.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这一条在法院 我个人 以及我们大家看来\N{\fs30}which the courts and myself
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.70,0:05:59.98,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还是挺合理的\N{\fs30}and we all feel is pretty reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.98,0:06:04.78,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(82,426)}杰瑞德·莱托回击EMI 暗示有黑幕\N{\c&H0304D7&}援引劳动法条款
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.32,0:06:06.98,Artifact,,0,0,0,,2008年7月4日 我们向EMI递交了解约书\N{\fs30}On July 4th 2008, we sent a termination letter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.29,0:06:09.79,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们援引了“7年条例”\N{\fs30}to EMI. We sighted the 7-year statute
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.79,0:06:13.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,从而合法地解除了我们与该公司的合同关系\N{\fs30}which legally ended our contract with the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:14.69,注人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(830,456)}2008年七月4日后 我们将不再隶属
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.32,0:06:15.43,Artifact,,0,0,0,,任何诉讼来讲\N{\fs30}With any lawsuit,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.20,0:06:24.76,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(738,560)}前EMI旗下 Capitol音乐集团董事长
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.43,0:06:16.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,都有双方的说法\N{\fs30}there is two sides of the argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.09,0:06:19.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你方的说法是:\N{\fs30}Your side of the argument was:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.09,0:06:23.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们的合约不再有效了\N{\fs30}"Our contract is no longer valid
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.09,0:06:25.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"因为'7年条例' "\N{\fs30}because of the 7-year statute"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.33,0:06:26.37,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他方则说:\N{\fs30}and their side of it is:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.26,0:06:28.79,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"不 这是不适用的\N{\fs30}"No, that is not applicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.22,0:06:32.22,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"你承诺了制作若干唱片\N{\fs30}You have a commitment based on a number of albums,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.22,0:06:34.27,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们也投入了相应的资金\N{\fs30}based on the amount of money we've spent
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.27,0:06:37.45,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"你不能单方终止"\N{\fs30}and you're not free to terminate this."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.45,0:06:38.85,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这真是个大卫对战歌利亚的故事(以小战大)\N{\fs30}It really is David against Goliath
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.56,0:06:43.37,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1000,588)}作家、音乐记者
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.85,0:06:41.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,在这个案件上 唱片公司这个巨人歌利亚\N{\fs30}and... and in this case the label,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.46,0:06:43.43,Artifact,,0,0,0,,打出了这个3000万美元的诉讼\N{\fs30}the Goliath was well, here's a 30 Million Dollars lawsuit
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.43,0:06:45.76,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我要让你夜不能寐" 他们不...\N{\fs30}like I am just gonna keep you awake, they don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.76,0:06:46.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们自己不会因为打这个天价官司..\N{\fs30}It doesn't keep them awake
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:47.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,..而睡不着觉 他们就是:\N{\fs30}suing for 30 Million Dollars, it's just:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.90,0:06:50.49,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我要在精神上和财务上把你搞垮\N{\fs30}I'm just stress you out, you know, emotionally
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.49,0:06:52.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,直到你投降\N{\fs30}and financially until you cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.96,0:06:59.07,地名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(658,416)}诉讼第1天
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.80,0:07:01.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,3000万美元\N{\fs30}30 Million Dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.20,0:07:04.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\fs30}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.51,0:07:05.57,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我觉得 这疯了吧\N{\fs30}I think, it's so crazy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.88,0:07:07.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我都搞太不明白啊\N{\fs30}that it doesn't even really register with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:14.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,怎么就特么 这么大个天文数字\N{\fs30}Like it's so fuckin' like just fantastically huge
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.33,0:07:17.95,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这都让我 不明白啊\N{\fs30}that I don't really get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.42,0:07:22.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你想想 就算咱赢了\N{\fs30}You would hope that, in success,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.14,0:07:23.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们会不会主动来改条款:\N{\fs30}that they would even take the initiative to be:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.86,0:07:25.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"好了 你们看,\N{\fs30}Okay look, you guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.40,0:07:28.00,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"你们签的合同确实够糟糕,\N{\fs30}you have the worst record deal on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.30,0:07:29.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"咱们来改一改\N{\fs30}Let's make this right
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:31.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们也知道 总有一天\N{\fs30}because we know at some point
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.75,0:07:33.73,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"你们自己会明白过来\N{\fs30}you're gonna educate yourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.73,0:07:35.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"你们会知道你们受到了剥削\N{\fs30}you're gonna realize that you've been stolen from
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.96,0:07:37.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"你们受到了要挟."\N{\fs30}and you've been hijacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.50,0:07:38.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们才不会那样\N{\fs30}They don't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.38,0:07:38.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不会\N{\fs30}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.11,0:07:40.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们会让艺人找他们改\N{\fs30}They make the artist do that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.40,0:07:41.89,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们才不管什么公平合理\N{\fs30}and they don't want to do what's fair, what's right,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.89,0:07:44.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你得拿法律武器震慑他们\N{\fs30}You have to threaten them with legal actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.08,0:07:46.76,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你制造审判先例 来震慑他们\N{\fs30}you have to threaten them with creating precedences
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.07,0:07:49.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这样才能从他们那儿得到\N{\fs30}in order to get them just to make
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.29,0:07:51.22,Artifact,,0,0,0,,些许公平 尽管他们仍然能够\N{\fs30}a slightly fair deal that still leaves them
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.22,0:07:53.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,分到绝大部分的利润\N{\fs30}with the complete lion share of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.84,0:07:55.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而且依然能完全掌控\N{\fs30}and the complete domination
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.74,0:07:58.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,三十秒上火星\N{\fs30}of Thirty Seconds to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.76,0:08:05.26,Artifact,,0,0,0,,乐感 是人类在子宫里就产生\N{\fs30}Musical taste actually begins to form in the womb,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.56,0:08:09.53,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(70,554)}神经学家 <音乐中的大脑>作者
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.68,0:08:08.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,在胎儿时期就完全形成了的\N{\fs30}the developing fetus has a fully functioning
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.68,0:08:11.36,Artifact,,0,0,0,,在20周的时候就有完善的听觉系统了\N{\fs30}auditory system at 20 weeks and is hearing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.36,0:08:14.01,Artifact,,0,0,0,,可以听到环境中的所有声音\N{\fs30}all of the sounds of the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:15.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,音乐无处不在\N{\fs30}Music is everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:18.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,真是丝丝渗透进我们每日的生活当中\N{\fs30}It's really woven into the fabric of everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.03,0:08:21.21,Artifact,,0,0,0,,感知研究显示,\N{\fs30}Perceptual studies have shown that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.50,0:08:25.84,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(674,554)}前EMI旗下 Capitol音乐集团 首席执行官
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.21,0:08:22.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,在较高的人类需求层次中\N{\fs30}in the higher hierarchy of needs,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.61,0:08:24.79,Artifact,,0,0,0,,人们最关心的两件事就是\N{\fs30}the two things that people care most about,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.79,0:08:26.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,音乐和性\N{\fs30}are music and sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.29,0:08:28.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所以毫无疑问\N{\fs30}So, there is no question
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.16,0:08:30.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,音乐是一项首要需求\N{\fs30}that music is a primal need
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:34.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,拥有难以置信的能量\N{\fs30}and it's unbelievably powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.37,0:08:36.79,Artifact,,0,0,0,,没有其他的艺术形式像音乐一样\N{\fs30}No other art form works like music.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.18,0:08:40.94,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1064,586)}音乐制作人
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.33,0:08:38.37,Artifact,,0,0,0,,绘画很美丽\N{\fs30}Paintings are beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.37,0:08:40.35,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但你懂的 一旦你看到它\N{\fs30}but, you know, once you see it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.35,0:08:43.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,最后你总会获知其表现的所有内容\N{\fs30}eventually you see everything in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.16,0:08:45.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但音乐不同 它是不断变化的\N{\fs30}With music, it's forever changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.08,0:08:47.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,一件音乐作品要想成功\N{\fs30}For a piece of music to succeed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.16,0:08:48.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就要能够让你进入\N{\fs30}it has to take you through
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.29,0:08:49.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,某种情感的历程\N{\fs30}some kind of emotional journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.99,0:08:51.54,Artifact,,0,0,0,,正确的和声序列\N{\fs30}The right chord sequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.54,0:08:52.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,歌曲的时间编排\N{\fs30}the right few seconds of a song
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.75,0:08:53.83,Artifact,,0,0,0,,都要体现出来\N{\fs30}and you are right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.66,0:08:56.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我就是这样感觉的\N{\fs30}That's exactly how I feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.34,0:08:58.82,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我喜欢尽力去诠释出\N{\fs30}I love in trying to interpret what
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.82,0:09:01.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,一首音乐 在词和曲双方面的内涵\N{\fs30}the music is saying both lyrically and musically,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.60,0:09:02.67,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么我爱音乐\N{\fs30}that's why I like music
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.11,0:09:04.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,当我读懂的时候\N{\fs30}and once I've tried to figure it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:07.71,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我的内心会充满狂喜\N{\fs30}I have personally crazy fantasies of what
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.71,0:09:08.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,想象音乐人在写歌时\N{\fs30}the person was thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.80,0:09:09.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是怎么想的\N{\fs30}when they wrote that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.58,0:09:10.39,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们为什么写这首歌\N{\fs30}and why they wrote that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.39,0:09:11.89,Artifact,,0,0,0,,以及它与我的关联\N{\fs30}and how does it relate to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.89,0:09:13.06,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这就是音乐\N{\fs30}That's what music is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.06,0:09:14.47,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你正确地把握了时间 歌词\N{\fs30}You mix the right word at the right time
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.47,0:09:17.82,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这样歌曲就以一种美妙\N{\fs30}with something that's beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.82,0:09:19.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,感人的方式\N{\fs30}and moving and sort of.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.47,0:09:23.57,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(68,584)}梦魇乐队 主唱
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.74,0:09:21.22,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这让你感到\N{\fs30}That makes you, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.22,0:09:22.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,汗毛都立起来了\N{\fs30}the hair on the back of your neck stand up,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.50,0:09:23.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,真是个难忘的时刻\N{\fs30}it's an incredible moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.08,0:09:25.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我想这就是为什么我们需要音乐\N{\fs30}That's probably why we need it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.30,0:09:26.63,Artifact,,0,0,0,,因为它太美好了\N{\fs30}because it's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.98,0:09:28.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,一首歌有它的故事\N{\fs30}The song has a story in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.19,0:09:31.49,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1036,586)}音乐人/技师
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.14,0:09:29.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,有它的心脏\N{\fs30}there is a heart behind it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.34,0:09:30.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,其中有频率\N{\fs30}there is a frequency within it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.55,0:09:32.10,Artifact,,0,0,0,,有作为人类的思考\N{\fs30}and you, as a person, delivered it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.10,0:09:33.48,Artifact,,0,0,0,,因此人们才在乎音乐\N{\fs30}and that why people care.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.48,0:09:36.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,音乐是全世界最强大的媒介\N{\fs30}Music is the most powerful vehicle in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.21,0:09:37.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,没说的\N{\fs30}Period.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.42,0:09:44.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,尽管有诉讼\N{\fs30}Despite the lawsuit,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.46,0:09:45.87,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们还是决定要继续\N{\fs30}we decided to move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.87,0:09:47.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,开始做我们的新专辑\N{\fs30}and start making our new album.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.00,0:09:49.87,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这就意味着 要我们自己出钱\N{\fs30}And that meant financing it ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.41,0:09:51.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,于是我们在好莱坞山房子的地下室里\N{\fs30}So, we built a studio in the basement
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.10,0:09:53.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,建起了录音室\N{\fs30}of the house in the Hollywood Hills,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:55.41,Artifact,,0,0,0,,雇来了Flood 开始了制作\N{\fs30}hired Flood and began the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.51,0:10:05.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,Flood就像是 音乐制作人中的巨星\N{\fs30}Flood is like this superstar producer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.14,0:10:07.56,Artifact,,0,0,0,,传奇人物 他制作了那么多的\N{\fs30}A legend. A guy that has made albums
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.56,0:10:08.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,经典专辑\N{\fs30}that will live forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.94,0:10:10.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,20年来 我一直在听他的作品\N{\fs30}I mean 20 years I've been listening to his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.81,0:10:13.54,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我常常翻到一张专辑、CD、录像带的背面\N{\fs30}I used to look on the back of albums and CDs
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.84,0:10:16.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,看到 "这个Flood是谁啊？"\N{\fs30}and tapes and who is this guy Flood?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.14,0:10:17.45,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我都不知道这是不是人名\N{\fs30}I didn't even know if he was a real person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.45,0:10:20.01,Artifact,,0,0,0,,因为只能看见这么个神秘简短的名字 Flood\N{\fs30}You always see this mysterious little name Flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:21.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他制作了Depeche Mode乐队,\N{\fs30}He produced Depeche Mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.48,0:10:23.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,U2.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.28,0:10:24.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,九寸钉\N{\fs30}Nine Inch Nails
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.32,0:10:25.43,Artifact,,0,0,0,,波莉·简·哈维\N{\fs30}PJ Harvey
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.65,0:10:26.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,...碎南瓜的专辑\N{\fs30}Smashing Pumpkins
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.60,0:10:29.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,当然 以及最重要的 显然是\N{\fs30}and the most important, obviously, is:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.60,0:10:31.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们三十秒上火星 所以...\N{\fs30}Thirty Seconds to Mars, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.22,0:10:34.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他极富创意\N{\fs30}His wide range of creativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.43,0:10:36.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,鼓舞人心\N{\fs30}it's inspiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.47,0:10:42.14,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(70,698)}音乐制作人
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.14,0:10:39.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,对我来说 创意就是 弱点 与冒险\N{\fs30}For me creativity is about vulnerability, taking risks,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.78,0:10:45.26,Artifact,,0,0,0,,融入真实的情感\N{\fs30}showing one's true emotion
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.48,0:10:49.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,让每一个艺人都切身感受到\N{\fs30}and to be able to make everybody feel as though
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.77,0:10:51.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们可以犯错误\N{\fs30}they can make mistakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.56,0:10:54.71,Artifact,,0,0,0,,可以不顾一切\N{\fs30}they can put themselves out there
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.02,0:10:56.87,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不会有人相互指责\N{\fs30}and there's no recriminations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.30,0:11:01.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,Jared冒了很大风险\N{\fs30}Jared took on a huge responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.38,0:11:04.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,肩负重担 他选择不与唱片公司合作\N{\fs30}and a huge burden when he chose to start making
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.60,0:11:06.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,独立制作<全面开战>\N{\fs30}"This is War" without a label on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.78,0:11:10.76,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他也不知道乐队的前景会怎样\N{\fs30}He didn't know what the future held for the band.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.42,0:11:12.49,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这很可怕\N{\fs30}It was very scary because
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.49,0:11:14.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他当时跟我说:\N{\fs30}he was letting me know like:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.28,0:11:16.37,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"你看 只有咱们自己\N{\fs30}"Look, we are alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.37,0:11:18.21,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"不会有外部资金\N{\fs30}There ain't gonna be any money coming in,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.21,0:11:20.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"不管是咱们作为乐队 还是我个人\N{\fs30}whatever we, as a band, or really me, Jared,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.84,0:11:26.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"作为乐队领袖 在乐队过去的收入中攒下的钱\N{\fs30}as like the leader, did good business to save some of the money that we made,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.32,0:11:28.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"这都不够咱们做专辑\N{\fs30}that's now going to pay for our album
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.40,0:11:30.24,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"和请制作人和工作人员的\N{\fs30}and our producer and our studio
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.54,0:11:34.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"这最后很有可能变成 0美元（破产）"\N{\fs30}which may result in zero Dollars."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.47,0:11:37.62,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们只能全靠我们自己\N{\fs30}We had to bet on ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.96,0:11:39.43,Artifact,,0,0,0,,用赌城的行话来打比方,\N{\fs30}even using Vegas terminology:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.43,0:11:41.48,Artifact,,0,0,0,,好像我们就是黑色方格\N{\fs30}it's like if we are the black square,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.48,0:11:44.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们把全部身家押到黑上\N{\fs30}we put everything on black and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.08,0:11:46.06,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后掷骰子\N{\fs30}we roll the dice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.50,0:11:57.96,地名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(466,400)}诉讼第14天
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.26,0:12:03.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们要去 见我们的经理人Irving Azoff\N{\fs30}We are heading to see our manager Irving Azoff
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.67,0:12:05.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,和我们的律师Peter Paterno\N{\fs30}and our lawyer Peter Paterno.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.05,0:12:10.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你好吗\N{\fs30}How are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.70,0:12:11.48,Artifact,,0,0,0,,好\N{\fs30}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.73,0:12:13.13,Artifact,,0,0,0,,好吧 你想怎么样\N{\fs30}Okay, what do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.66,0:12:14.65,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我想的就是:\N{\fs30}What I would like to happen is:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.65,0:12:15.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我想上法庭\N{\fs30}I would like to go to court,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.96,0:12:18.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我想站在由我的同行组成的陪审团面前\N{\fs30}I'd like to sit in front of a jury of my peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.07,0:12:22.33,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(74,696)}乐队经理人
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.99,0:12:22.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我觉得就算是最无争议的诉讼\N{\fs30}I think in any lawsuit that's a slam-dunk,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.70,0:12:24.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还是有20%的几率会出问题\N{\fs30}you still have a 20% chance you get screwed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.08,0:12:27.63,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我先问个大方向的问题\N{\fs30}Let me ask you a big picture question:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.44,0:12:32.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,跟传统的唱片公司签约...\N{\fs30}Signing a record deal with a traditional
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.61,0:12:34.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还是不签？\N{\fs30}record company or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.12,0:12:36.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,有没有别的选择?\N{\fs30}What are the other options?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.65,0:12:38.82,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我的意见一向是\N{\fs30}My view has always been that any deal that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.82,0:12:41.25,Artifact,,0,0,0,,跟小厂牌公司签的合约\N{\fs30}doesn't involve a major record label is better
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.25,0:12:43.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,比跟大厂牌公司签约要好\N{\fs30}than any deal any major label will offer you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.88,0:12:46.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,因为你有自主权 自己说了算\N{\fs30}because you have your ownership, you're masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.14,0:12:48.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,其他的事也是一样 你得记住\N{\fs30}The other issue too, that you have to keep in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.29,0:12:49.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就算你跟别的公司\N{\fs30}is that even if you signed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.42,0:12:50.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,签了合约\N{\fs30}with one of these other alternatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.53,0:12:52.83,Artifact,,0,0,0,,EMI还是要告你\N{\fs30}EMI is still suing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.20,0:12:54.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,看来咱们的情况不容乐观\N{\fs30}It seems that we're between a rock and a hard place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.86,0:12:58.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,要么签个恐龙时代的超级老套合约...\N{\fs30}Either signed some antiquated dinosaur deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.19,0:13:00.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但是 就没有新模式吗？\N{\fs30}But what's the new model of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.60,0:13:03.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,新模式更差\N{\fs30}The new model is worse, so the antiquated
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.04,0:13:04.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,恐龙级超老合约 还是可行的\N{\fs30}dinosaur deal is a good deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.66,0:13:06.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,为什么没有更好的新模式？\N{\fs30}Why there isn't a new model that's better?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.10,0:13:08.93,Artifact,,0,0,0,,听音乐的人前所未有的多啊！\N{\fs30}People are listening to music more than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.38,0:13:10.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,因为我们都在赔钱\N{\fs30}Cause they're all losing money.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.44,0:13:12.21,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们不买\N{\fs30}They're not buying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.21,0:13:13.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们也许听了\N{\fs30}They may be listening but
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.16,0:13:14.10,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但他们不买\N{\fs30}they're not buying it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.22,0:13:15.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们不付钱\N{\fs30}they're not paying for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.83,0:13:17.63,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(64,694)}乐队律师
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.30,0:13:16.74,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这样（音乐）甚至更不值钱了\N{\fs30}It makes it even less valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.39,0:13:18.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如果我们面对的是传统的唱片公司\N{\fs30}If it were a traditional record company
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.03,0:13:20.15,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还用坐在这儿干嘛\N{\fs30}we wouldn't be sitting here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.15,0:13:21.53,Artifact,,0,0,0,,早就解决了\N{\fs30}we would have settle that a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.53,0:13:23.53,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但现在时运不好\N{\fs30}We drew a bad card.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.53,0:13:25.25,Artifact,,0,0,0,,咱们面对的是一个外行\N{\fs30}We drew a guy from outside the business
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.25,0:13:27.25,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他不按行业规矩来\N{\fs30}who doesn't play by industry rules,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.25,0:13:28.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他也不在乎\N{\fs30}who doesn't give a shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.72,0:13:30.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不能跟他们调解？\N{\fs30}We can't get them to settle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.57,0:13:32.43,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们现在不会跟咱调解 他们跟我说:\N{\fs30}They're not gonna settle now. They said to me:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.78,0:13:34.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我不管这官司打多长时间\N{\fs30}"I don't care how long it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.22,0:13:37.49,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"不管别的唱片公司多么生气\N{\fs30}I don't care how angry it makes the other label groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.54,0:13:40.73,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我都要求开庭审理"\N{\fs30}I would go to court to a decision."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.89,0:13:46.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,唱片产业处在一个非常非常不利的境地\N{\fs30}The record business is in a very very serious trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.32,0:13:47.72,Artifact,,0,0,0,,看看历史上那些已经消失的行业\N{\fs30}If you look at historically other businesses
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.05,0:13:51.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你就会知道\N{\fs30}that have gone away,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.05,0:13:53.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我认为它就是在逐渐的衰退\N{\fs30}I think there is this kind of gradual decline...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.68,0:13:55.74,Artifact,,0,0,0,,呃 不是"逐渐" 其实衰退得挺厉害的 像这样\N{\fs30}Well gradual, it has been pretty severe, but like this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.40,0:13:58.65,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后它遇到了一个拐点\N{\fs30}and then it just reaches a kind of tipping point
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.65,0:13:59.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,于是就跳水了\N{\fs30}and just falls off the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.52,0:14:05.10,Artifact,,0,0,0,,唱片产业的盈利模式\N{\fs30}The economics around the record business
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.32,0:14:08.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就是卖专辑\N{\fs30}is based on selling albums.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.34,0:14:13.65,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(64,552)}洛杉矶KROQ电台  音乐总监
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.88,0:14:11.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你知道 小时候 你必须得买下整张专辑\N{\fs30}You know growing up you had to buy the entire album
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.16,0:14:12.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,才能听到里面你喜欢的那首歌 不买不行\N{\fs30}to get the song you loved, you had to!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.13,0:14:13.95,Artifact,,0,0,0,,没别的办法\N{\fs30}You had no choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.34,0:14:15.67,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而现在却是\N{\fs30}And now, what happens is:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.68,0:14:18.49,Artifact,,0,0,0,,孩子呆在家里 说:\N{\fs30}A kid is sitting at home and goes:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.49,0:14:20.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,“我一定得听Kings And Queens这首歌”\N{\fs30}"I've got to hear that Kings and Queens song,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.62,0:14:21.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,“一定要听”\N{\fs30}I got to hear that!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.62,0:14:24.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们不用去开车 或是求父母\N{\fs30}They don't have to get in a car or ask their parents
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.77,0:14:26.57,Artifact,,0,0,0,,攒上个12块钱才能去买\N{\fs30}and save up 12 bucks to go buy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:28.43,Artifact,,0,0,0,,现在你有了选择\N{\fs30}Now you're given a choice and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.43,0:14:29.87,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你可以只买你爱的一首歌\N{\fs30}you can buy the song you love
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.87,0:14:31.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不用买整张专辑 你会选哪种呢\N{\fs30}without buying the album, you gonna do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.15,0:14:35.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这都不止 你甚至可以 免费得到\N{\fs30}not only that, when you can buy... Have it for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.07,0:14:41.97,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(464,258)}音乐消逝的十年：销售额减半
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.67,0:14:39.74,Artifact,,0,0,0,,唱片的销量 在过去的六年里\N{\fs30}Record sales have dipped 20% a year
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.74,0:14:41.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,每年都减少20%\N{\fs30}for the last 6 years, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.77,0:14:43.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这极为严重\N{\fs30}That's a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.71,0:14:47.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,音乐产业真的遭到了重创\N{\fs30}The music business has really become decimated
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.89,0:14:50.45,Artifact,,0,0,0,,很大一部分原因就是人们都去非法下载了\N{\fs30}and it has been largely because of illegal downloads.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.82,0:14:52.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,当然也有别的因素\N{\fs30}Others factors too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.36,0:14:54.00,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但我们面临的环境就是\N{\fs30}But the predicament we're in now, is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.00,0:14:57.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,整整一代的音乐听众\N{\fs30}that an entire generation of music listeners,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.32,0:15:00.62,Artifact,,0,0,0,,基本上所有21岁以下的人群\N{\fs30}virtually everybody under the age of 21,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.62,0:15:02.52,Artifact,,0,0,0,,从小到大\N{\fs30}has grown up in a world
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.52,0:15:04.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,从记事起\N{\fs30}where, for their entire sentient lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.35,0:15:06.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,在他们的世界里 从没为听音乐花过钱\N{\fs30}they've never had to pay for music.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.23,0:15:09.22,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而当他们看到我这个年龄的\N{\fs30}And they look at people my age and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.22,0:15:11.82,Artifact,,0,0,0,,买专辑的人 他们就认为我们真傻啊\N{\fs30}who buy music they think we're saps.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.34,0:15:14.37,Artifact,,0,0,0,,“你为什么要花钱买免费的东西？”\N{\fs30}Why would you pay for something that's free?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.68,0:15:16.36,Artifact,,0,0,0,,“这就跟花钱买空气一样啊！”\N{\fs30}It would be like paying for air!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:21.30,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(942,584)}"林肯公园"乐队主唱
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:18.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我记得好像是Trent Reznor说过:\N{\fs30}I've heard someone like Trent Reznor say:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:18.05,注释,,0,0,0,,(注: Nine Inch Nails九寸钉乐队主唱)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.05,0:15:20.69,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"你知道 你辛辛苦苦花了一整年做这个\N{\fs30}"You know, you work for a fucking year on something,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.40,0:15:23.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"投入了这么多时间 这么多钱\N{\fs30}and you put all this time and you spend all this money
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.97,0:15:27.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"用来创作...这些歌\N{\fs30}on creating these songs
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.40,0:15:31.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"然后你买杯咖啡 却比这歌还贵"\N{\fs30}and a cup of coffee buys you the day, cost more than your song."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.64,0:15:33.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,消费者不会走进食品店\N{\fs30}Consumers wouldn't walk into a grocery store,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.55,0:15:35.24,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后偷一条面包 据为己有\N{\fs30}and steal a loaf of bread and have it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.24,0:15:37.22,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但偷音乐就没事\N{\fs30}but it became okay to steal music.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.33,0:15:40.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这真不是唱片公司的问题\N{\fs30}That really isn't something you blame the labels for,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.23,0:15:43.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你懂的 这是科技\N{\fs30}you know, that's technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:48.57,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(834,580)}System of a Down乐队主唱
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.39,0:15:46.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,唱片公司从来没能有力地凝聚起来\N{\fs30}The labels have never been cohesive enough to create
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.50,0:15:48.12,Artifact,,0,0,0,,建立他们自己未来的分销渠道\N{\fs30}to create their own future distribution systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.12,0:15:49.87,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所以才让一家电脑公司抢了先\N{\fs30}Which is why it took a computer company
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.87,0:15:53.06,Artifact,,0,0,0,,建立了iTunes 嗯.. 而如果他们(唱片公司)够聪明\N{\fs30}to start iTunes, Have they've been smart enough
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.06,0:15:55.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们自己也能联合建立类似iTunes的音乐渠道\N{\fs30}they would have co-owned their own digital delivery
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.58,0:15:58.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,(iTunes)真是把一切都搅乱了\N{\fs30}like iTunes, you know, that was a big mess up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.70,0:16:01.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,当苹果公司——它是个很棒的公司\N{\fs30}When Apple, which is a great company,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.16,0:16:03.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,别误会——它是美国第三大的公司\N{\fs30}don't get me wrong, is the third largest company in America
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.81,0:16:05.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,也是美国最大的音乐经销商\N{\fs30}and the biggest music retailer in America,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.02,0:16:09.25,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我觉得这才是人们担忧的\N{\fs30}I think that's concerning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.83,0:16:10.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,它生产的不是音乐 而是设备\N{\fs30}It's a device manufacturer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.47,0:16:13.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,唱片公司被惊呆了 也吓坏了\N{\fs30}The labels are petrified and terrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.97,0:16:15.17,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们不明白怎么回事\N{\fs30}They don't know what's going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.17,0:16:16.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们都搞不懂自己的行业了\N{\fs30}they don't even understand their own industry anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.68,0:16:18.72,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们规模太大 发展太慢 所以...\N{\fs30}they've been too big and too slow to change, so
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:20.72,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我觉得它们势必有一天会瓦解\N{\fs30}I do think they're just gonna start to crumble.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.49,0:16:36.83,地名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(624,398)}诉讼第30天
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.43,0:16:51.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,咱们开始Kings And Queens吧\N{\fs30}Let's play "Kings and Queens"...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.89,0:17:30.54,Artifact,,0,0,0,,里面肯定有点问题\N{\fs30}There is definitely something in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.67,0:17:31.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,再来一次\N{\fs30}let's try it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.27,0:17:36.92,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我觉得就是这段   -我也觉得\N{\fs30}I think this is the part (I think so too)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.92,0:17:40.36,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我坐在那儿 在脑海里唱着\N{\fs30}I'm sitting here... I'm singing it in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.36,0:17:42.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,充满感染力 我还想听这样的片段\N{\fs30}It's infectious, I want to hear it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.43,0:17:44.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那个吉他声放出来 我是说...\N{\fs30}That guitar creeping up... I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.11,0:17:45.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,好哎 对\N{\fs30}Great. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.93,0:17:48.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我知道 做这样的专辑,\N{\fs30}So, I know, for making records like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.46,0:17:53.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,工作量很大 很难 这都是必经之路\N{\fs30}the hard work, the struggle is all part of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.68,0:17:55.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,重点是你们要忠于自己的感觉\N{\fs30}it's about being truthful to yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.15,0:17:57.41,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我觉得现在就是这样\N{\fs30}That's what I mean about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.81,0:18:00.93,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你可以跟着感觉 拥抱它\N{\fs30}It's like you can take it and embrace it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.34,0:18:02.11,Artifact,,0,0,0,,把它展现出来\N{\fs30}And go with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.32,0:18:06.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,失去点平衡 疯狂一下\N{\fs30}Be a bit off balance, try out a few mad things
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.90,0:18:08.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你们现在的状况完全可以\N{\fs30}and there you are in a great place to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.69,0:18:38.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,在这期间\N{\fs30}In the middle of all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.14,0:18:41.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们收到了一条好消息:\N{\fs30}we got some good news: we were nominated
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.81,0:18:44.53,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们得到了拉丁MTV音乐奖的提名\N{\fs30}for a Latin MTV award.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.63,0:18:46.56,Artifact,,0,0,0,,于是我们打点行装 飞到了墨西哥\N{\fs30}So we packed our bags and flew ourselves to Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.70,0:19:20.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们正在工作室里努力...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.70,0:19:23.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,同往常一样激动
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.70,0:19:28.20,Artifact,,0,0,0,,内心充满热情与快乐 终于能够制作新歌了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.20,0:19:31.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我是Flavor Flav(演员) 我旁边是Tomo 还有其他的哥们\N{\fs30}Flavor Flav here with Tomo, and the motherf******* boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.80,0:19:33.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如假特么的包换！\N{\fs30}The real f**king McCoys!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.50,0:19:39.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,虽然大家都说俺们是明星\N{\fs30}Even though everybody classify us as stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.70,0:19:43.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但俺们是从三十秒上他娘的火星来的!\N{\fs30}but we are 30 Seconds from Motherf******g Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.20,0:20:08.52,Artifact,,0,0,0,,过了一个超级兴奋 难忘的夜晚\N{\fs30}After an exciting and unforgettable night,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:11.82,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们醒来发现 我们收到了\N{\fs30}we woke up to discover that we had been served
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.82,0:20:14.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,EMI的法律文书\N{\fs30}with legal papers from EMI.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.84,0:20:19.63,Artifact,,0,0,0,,EMI要求我们提供所有邮件 所有文件 所有的样歌
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.63,0:20:24.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所有的歌曲思路 2008年7月4日前写成的 所有歌词
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.03,0:20:29.63,Artifact,,0,0,0,,被告 杰瑞德·莱托和珊农·莱托 官方又称
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.63,0:20:30.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,三十秒上火星
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.34,0:20:35.45,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们现在想查我们的电脑 我们的...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.63,0:20:41.20,Artifact,,0,0,0,,...硬盘 我们的黑莓手机 查找任何有利于他们的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.24,0:20:44.66,Artifact,,0,0,0,,现在的势头就是 他们要赢 我们要输
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.66,0:20:49.00,Artifact,,0,0,0,,现在不是对错的问题 也不是发展 成功 的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.00,0:20:51.00,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我想知道是整个公司都这么想
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.42,0:20:48.97,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(68,128)}管理人员
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.20,0:20:52.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还是只有公司高层？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.50,0:20:55.82,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是新的人员进来了 说：“好了 咱们的问题在哪？”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.82,0:20:57.76,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而这是困境之一
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.76,0:21:00.26,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们就是想要摆脱困境
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.81,0:21:07.47,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你一定要理解 整个事\N{\fs30}You have to understand this whole story
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.47,0:21:09.36,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是完全发生在我们新专辑制作之前的\N{\fs30}really began before we started the album.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.93,0:21:11.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,在我们成为被告之前\N{\fs30}Before we got sued,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.80,0:21:14.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们还与EMI有着友好的谈判关系\N{\fs30}when we were in friendly renegotiations with EMI.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.74,0:21:17.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,谈判进行的很顺利\N{\fs30}And that was going well,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.39,0:21:18.67,Artifact,,0,0,0,,Irving(经理人)在与他们协商\N{\fs30}Irving was talking to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.86,0:21:27.23,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(978,590)}前EMI首席财务官
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.42,0:21:21.57,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们达成了一些成果\N{\fs30}We had met some efforts to address some commercial
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.57,0:21:23.31,Artifact,,0,0,0,,与30stm达成了一些商业协议\N{\fs30}terms of the Thirty Seconds to Mars agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.31,0:21:26.15,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这些协议 我们回头想想\N{\fs30}that I think, we all recognized,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.15,0:21:29.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,可能是...不太合适\N{\fs30}were probably inappropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.25,0:21:35.12,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后 就出了问题\N{\fs30}And then, something happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.72,0:21:40.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,谈判没戏了 出于各种原因吧\N{\fs30}That effort stalled out for whatever reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.78,0:21:43.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,再过不久 投资人就要连\N{\fs30}Soon investors won't be able
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.09,0:21:44.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,甲壳虫乐队的歌也买不起了\N{\fs30}to buy a piece of the Beatles.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.92,0:21:47.45,Artifact,,0,0,0,,百代EMI下个月将变为私有制\N{\fs30}EMI is going private next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.45,0:21:49.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,该英国音乐出版商将被收购\N{\fs30}The British music publisher is being acquired
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.78,0:21:52.25,Artifact,,0,0,0,,价格高达近50亿美元\N{\fs30}for nearly 5 Billion Dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.25,0:21:58.77,网页,,0,0,0,,{\c&H896548&\pos(694,408)}泰丰资本成功竞购EMI
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.53,0:21:56.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,泰丰资本 是一家位于英国的私募股权投资公司\N{\fs30}Terra Firma is an UK based private equity company.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.72,0:22:00.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,专门收购陷入困境的公司,\N{\fs30}They tent to buy companies that are distressed,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.98,0:22:04.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这些公司并不一定来自陷入困境的行业\N{\fs30}not necessarily companies that are in distressed industries,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.17,0:22:06.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这一点对于EMI的案例很重要\N{\fs30}which is important point when you come back around EMI.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.42,0:22:07.65,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如果你是英国人 你一定会这样想EMI:\N{\fs30}If you are in England, I imagine you look at EMI:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.65,0:22:09.10,Artifact,,0,0,0,,它是甲壳虫乐队的老家\N{\fs30}it's the home of the Beatles,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.10,0:22:12.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,它是英国最为标志性的公司\N{\fs30}it's is one of the most iconic British companies ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.81,0:22:15.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你会对自己说: "哇 我肯定也能把它弄好,\N{\fs30}And you say to yourself: "Wow! I can fix that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.50,0:22:19.39,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"那帮蠢材 他们肯定不懂经营"\N{\fs30}Those dummies, I'm sure that they don't know what they're doing either.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.39,0:22:22.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"所以 我把它买下来好了 让它起死回生"\N{\fs30}So, let me buy that and turn it around."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.09,0:22:25.45,Artifact,,0,0,0,,泰丰资本的真正的领导者是Guy Hands\N{\fs30}The real principal of Terra Firma is Guy Hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.09,0:22:27.35,注人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(552,514)}葛涵思 泰丰资本创始人
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.45,0:22:27.06,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他基本上掌控着泰丰资本的运营\N{\fs30}he's essentially the guy who runs Terra Firma.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.06,0:22:30.37,Artifact,,0,0,0,,Guy Hands是个白手起家的亿万富翁\N{\fs30}Guy Hands, he is a self-made billionaire.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.37,0:22:32.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他真是难以置信的成功\N{\fs30}He's been incredibly successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.89,0:22:33.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他有一次成功 是\N{\fs30}One of the victories he had was
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.85,0:22:38.23,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1032,582)}音乐产业作家
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.81,0:22:41.35,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他买下了北欧一条高速公路上所有的加油站,\N{\fs30}he bought all the gas stations on a highway in northern Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.55,0:22:44.73,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后把里面的洗手间 都清洁一新\N{\fs30}And he cleaned the bathrooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.12,0:22:47.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们清洁过之后 突然\N{\fs30}Once they cleaned them all of sudden
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.03,0:22:49.66,Artifact,,0,0,0,,加油站的生意就突飞猛进\N{\fs30}business went up at the gas stations,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.66,0:22:51.73,Artifact,,0,0,0,,附带的便利店也是日进斗金\N{\fs30}at the convenience stores attached to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.73,0:22:53.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,于是他就赚了大笔的钱\N{\fs30}And he made a ton of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.13,0:22:57.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们花几十亿美元来收购一个公司\N{\fs30}They spent billions of dollars on a company
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.34,0:23:00.49,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我认为 他们是真的坚信\N{\fs30}and I really think that they believed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.49,0:23:02.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,自己可以将之扭亏为盈的\N{\fs30}they could transform it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.07,0:23:04.79,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(532,266)}{\c&H370AAC&}葛涵思的泰丰资本
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.79,0:23:07.59,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(582,500)}泰丰资本24亿英镑收购百代EMI
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.24,0:23:07.20,Artifact,,0,0,0,,泰丰资本介入并收购EMI之后\N{\fs30}When Terra Firma came in and purchased EMI
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.20,0:23:09.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就开始了他们的扭转机制\N{\fs30}they became that benefactor regime
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.42,0:23:11.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,让我们赔3000万块钱\N{\fs30}that sued us for 30 Million bucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.71,0:23:14.64,Artifact,,0,0,0,,泰丰资本把我们从谈判桌上拉走\N{\fs30}Terra Firma took the negotiation away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.22,0:23:17.48,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我想他们是了解了这个事 然后说...\N{\fs30}I think they looked at it and they said,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.45,0:23:20.17,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我想他们不满意的是\N{\fs30}I think they didn't like the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.17,0:23:22.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们在友好谈判 这个事实\N{\fs30}that it was a friendly renegotiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.96,0:23:26.76,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们先入为主地认为 我们肯定不是省油的灯\N{\fs30}They came with a perspective of we've got to be hard-nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.70,0:23:46.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,录音 第一次\N{\fs30}Take one...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.96,0:24:01.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我起调没起好 再来一次\N{\fs30}I'm in a bad beginning... And again...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.54,0:24:09.20,Artifact,,0,0,0,,喔~~ 热起来了呢 哥们 再来一次\N{\fs30}Woo... It's getting warmed up, dude, one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.06,0:24:15.10,Artifact,,0,0,0,,好极了\N{\fs30}Perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.49,0:24:16.52,Artifact,,0,0,0,,咱再录2次\N{\fs30}Let's just do a couple of more
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.52,0:24:17.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后听听\N{\fs30}and then we'll listen
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.40,0:24:17.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,再一次\N{\fs30}One more...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.96,0:24:20.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,一次 最后一次 再来嘛...\N{\fs30}One last one... One Maaaas...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.70,0:24:22.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,等一下 我放松一下手\N{\fs30}Give me one second to loosen my hand up
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.14,0:24:27.98,Artifact,,0,0,0,,再一次... 好玩嘛\N{\fs30}One more... Just for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.09,0:24:30.67,Artifact,,0,0,0,,哥们 你还没到一百次呢\N{\fs30}Dude, you're still under a hundred takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.06,0:24:32.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,现在是97次\N{\fs30}You're at ninety seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.30,0:24:35.26,Artifact,,0,0,0,,97次? 好吧 妹的\N{\fs30}Ninety seven? Okay. Fuck that!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.48,0:24:36.56,Artifact,,0,0,0,,咱再来三次\N{\fs30}We're gonna do three more.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.68,0:24:37.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,好的 来吧\N{\fs30}Yes! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.56,0:24:41.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,等一下 我还没好呢\N{\fs30}Hold on... Let me get ready...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.58,0:24:44.35,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我从没遇到过 如此有动力\N{\fs30}I never met anyone as driven
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.35,0:24:45.74,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如此辛勤工作的人\N{\fs30}who will work this hard
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.74,0:24:47.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他会为了工作 你懂的\N{\fs30}who will go to the, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.75,0:24:49.39,Artifact,,0,0,0,,赴汤蹈火\N{\fs30}end of the earth and back,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.65,0:24:52.02,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就算只有百万分之一的机会也在所不惜\N{\fs30}just on a one and a million chance,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:53.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,只要是对音乐有好处\N{\fs30}that something is gonna help the music.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.15,0:24:57.62,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我认识的人里面 没有人\N{\fs30}There is nobody, that I know personally,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.97,0:25:00.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,能真正说 对自己的艺术 自己的工作 如此用心\N{\fs30}that can say that they do for their art and their work
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.84,0:25:02.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,像他一样\N{\fs30}what he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.25,0:25:05.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你问我 Jared在<全面开战>\N{\fs30}You ask me what Jared's role is
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.75,0:25:06.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,中是何种角色?\N{\fs30}in the making of This is War?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.97,0:25:08.24,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这个题目就太小了\N{\fs30}It's too small of a question
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.24,0:25:10.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,无法涵盖他在30STM世界里所做的工作\N{\fs30}to encompass what he does in the world of Thirty Seconds to Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.58,0:25:12.56,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他是乐队的灵魂\N{\fs30}He is the Mastermind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.00,0:25:20.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,即便是现在这样的成就\N{\fs30}Success on the level that we even have right now
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.03,0:25:26.35,Artifact,,0,0,0,,也是我们从来不敢想的 你无法...你怎么能想得到?\N{\fs30}we never dreamed. You couldn't... How could you dream of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.75,0:25:34.98,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我和我哥出生在路易斯安那州\N{\fs30}My brother and I were born in Louisiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.10,0:25:38.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们趟过密西西比河泥泞的岸边时\N{\fs30}We climbed out of the muddy banks of the Mississippi
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.44,0:25:40.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,一手拿着乐器\N{\fs30}with our instruments in one hand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.58,0:25:44.23,Artifact,,0,0,0,,另一手攥着满满的 食物救济券\N{\fs30}and... A fist full of food stamps in the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.05,0:25:46.65,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们的妈妈十分年轻\N{\fs30}We had a very young mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.41,0:25:48.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我想 她怀着我\N{\fs30}I think she was pregnant with me and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.68,0:25:51.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,带着我哥的时候 才18岁\N{\fs30}had my brother by the time she was 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.04,0:25:52.98,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我还是个孩子的时候 就有了孩子\N{\fs30}I was a child that had children.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.42,0:25:56.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我从没觉得有什么艰难\N{\fs30}I never considered that any of it was difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.78,0:25:59.64,Artifact,,0,0,0,,带着两个宝宝去上学\N{\fs30}Going to school with two babies and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.64,0:26:02.62,Artifact,,0,0,0,,领着救济金 靠着食物券\N{\fs30}being on welfare and having food stamps
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.18,0:26:03.98,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(939,588)}杰瑞德和珊农的母亲
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.62,0:26:03.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,和医疗补助卡过活\N{\fs30}and Medicaid cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.59,0:26:07.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,小的时候 家里穷\N{\fs30}When you are a kid and you're poor,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.72,0:26:09.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你也意识不到\N{\fs30}I don't think you realize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.87,0:26:12.00,Artifact,,0,0,0,,直到我长大了\N{\fs30}It wasn't until I got much older
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.00,0:26:13.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我才发现我们没钱出门\N{\fs30}I realized we didn't have money to go out
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.91,0:26:15.06,Artifact,,0,0,0,,买很多礼物\N{\fs30}buy a bunch of presents
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.46,0:26:17.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,每到圣诞节 我们都是\N{\fs30}Every Christmas was really about making
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.13,0:26:19.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,自己做礼物给对方的\N{\fs30}presents for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.92,0:26:22.48,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们小时候总是搬家\N{\fs30}We moved around quite a bit as kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.90,0:26:25.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们住一起时 总是有这些\N{\fs30}When we lived together it was always this thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.12,0:26:29.21,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(72,582)}莱托家的朋友、艺术家
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.40,0:26:27.73,Artifact,,0,0,0,,总是有事做\N{\fs30}there was always something going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.73,0:26:29.18,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们在做艺术 做音乐\N{\fs30}we were making art, making music.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.41,0:26:31.66,Artifact,,0,0,0,,周围总是有材料\N{\fs30}There was always things around,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.28,0:26:34.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,谁都可以随便捡起什么来 就地作画\N{\fs30}anybody could pick up and draw or paint with,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.48,0:26:37.11,Artifact,,0,0,0,,或是穿上奇装异服 跳舞唱歌\N{\fs30}and dress up and dance around and sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.14,0:26:39.66,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我是说 总有那种氛围\N{\fs30}I mean there was always that energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.87,0:26:40.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那种创作的氛围\N{\fs30}that creative energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.03,0:26:44.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们从小就生活在音乐的环境里\N{\fs30}They were indoctrinated into music quite really early.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.32,0:26:47.51,Artifact,,0,0,0,,到处是音乐 音乐 音乐 音乐\N{\fs30}It was like music, music, music, music.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.92,0:26:50.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我妈妈以前总在车里唱歌\N{\fs30}My mother used to sing in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.75,0:26:53.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我记得她常常跟着歌曲哼唱\N{\fs30}I remember she would harmonize with songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.89,0:26:57.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我记得那时觉得 她的声音好棒\N{\fs30}I remember thinking that she always had a great voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.94,0:27:00.56,Artifact,,0,0,0,,她总是在听音乐\N{\fs30}She was always listening to music
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.56,0:27:03.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,给我们听很多很棒的音乐\N{\fs30}and exposed us to a lot of great music.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.47,0:27:05.41,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我从没真正想过\N{\fs30}And I never really thought
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.41,0:27:08.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,自己有一天会成为做乐队的音乐人\N{\fs30}that you could be a musician in a band.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.11,0:27:10.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我从没想过要出名\N{\fs30}I never thought about fame,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.07,0:27:12.64,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我从没想过那些东西\N{\fs30}I never thought about any of that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.98,0:27:15.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们的童年 那段接触创作的经历\N{\fs30}That early childhood, that creative exposure
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.42,0:27:18.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,真正塑造了我和我哥\N{\fs30}really helped shape my brother and I
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.23,0:27:21.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,使我们受益匪浅\N{\fs30}in an important way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.68,0:27:36.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,嗯 我喜欢 听起来很棒\N{\fs30}Yeah, I like that, it sounds great.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.91,0:27:38.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我只是在想 桥段的部分我该怎么打？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.03,0:27:40.76,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这段确实是挺难\N{\fs30}It's definitely a tough place
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.76,0:27:42.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不容易打出花样来\N{\fs30}to play something different I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.77,0:27:44.39,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这段是怎么唱的?\N{\fs30}What do the vocals say?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.39,0:27:45.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,马上 高潮那段?\N{\fs30}Right away, when they go off?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.10,0:27:53.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,等等 我都不知道和声是啥样的\N{\fs30}Wait, I don't even know the chorus.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.85,0:28:08.35,Artifact,,0,0,0,,也别着急\N{\fs30}It's also no rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.35,0:28:10.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,咱们慢慢来就行\N{\fs30}We should just take the time it needs
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.04,0:28:10.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,把它弄好了\N{\fs30}to get it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.32,0:28:12.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如果咱们要做上三天\N{\fs30}And if we have to do it over 3 days,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.70,0:28:13.76,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那就做三天\N{\fs30}we'll do over 3 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.01,0:28:15.95,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我只是体会啊 我就... 你懂的\N{\fs30}I'm just in it. I just... You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.95,0:28:18.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后就 它就没了 哦老天 好吧\N{\fs30}And then, it's gone... Oh my god, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.42,0:28:19.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不 我知道了\N{\fs30}No, I got that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.04,0:28:21.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就是这样的 好了\N{\fs30}That's the way it is, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.37,0:28:23.82,Artifact,,0,0,0,,咱们相互鼓励 做的时候也享受这一过程吧\N{\fs30}Let's encourage each other to enjoy it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.09,0:28:24.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,发现之旅\N{\fs30}This discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.75,0:28:26.18,Artifact,,0,0,0,,因为东西很不错\N{\fs30}Because it's awesome stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.18,0:28:28.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你做的那个 小陷阱般的处理\N{\fs30}the feel that you came out with the snare,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.88,0:28:30.62,Artifact,,0,0,0,,特别酷 你以前从没做过\N{\fs30}totally cool and you never done it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.62,0:28:31.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,回头庆祝吧
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.83,0:28:34.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,咱们做的时候也欢乐一点吧\N{\fs30}Let have a bit of joy while we do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.19,0:28:38.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,好得很  工序不同嘛亲~\N{\fs30}That's all good... Different processes man.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.56,0:28:41.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我欢乐着呢\N{\fs30}I am enjoying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.16,0:28:44.26,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我耍到他了\N{\fs30}I got him all fooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.00,0:29:10.54,注人名,,0,0,0,,{\c&H344C19&\pos(392,326)}完成！
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.94,0:29:30.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们进展不错 但还有好多东西要做\N{\fs30}We getting there, but there's still lots to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.26,0:29:36.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我从没听过哪家唱片公司\N{\fs30}I never heard of a label
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.07,0:29:36.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是不坑艺人的\N{\fs30}that doesn't screw an artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.99,0:29:40.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你找哪个艺人跟唱片公司审计一下\N{\fs30}You talk to anybody who audits their label
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.35,0:29:41.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们(艺人)肯定是欠钱的\N{\fs30}they're always own money.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.51,0:29:44.06,Artifact,,0,0,0,,没特殊情况的话\N{\fs30}And if nothing else,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.06,0:29:45.89,Artifact,,0,0,0,,一般唱片公司都会攥着艺人的钱\N{\fs30}usually the label holds back enough money
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.89,0:29:47.43,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这样你审计的成本过高\N{\fs30}that your cost of auditing is such
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.43,0:29:48.93,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你就不会去审计了 所以..\N{\fs30}that you won't do it, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.46,0:29:52.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,商业模式就是这样 坑艺人来赚钱\N{\fs30}That's the business model is screwing the artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.32,0:29:54.53,Artifact,,0,0,0,,财务上的条款一直就是模糊不清的\N{\fs30}The financial practices have been shady
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.53,0:29:55.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,从一开始就是\N{\fs30}since the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.08,0:29:58.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,从爷爷辈的年代传下来 从五六十年代\N{\fs30}It's been grandfathered in since the 50's and 60's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.19,0:29:59.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,摇滚乐刚兴起时就是这样\N{\fs30}when rock and roll really started.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.00,0:30:03.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,从50年代 那时候他们就在坑艺人了\N{\fs30}In the 50's, they were screwing the artist then,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.46,0:30:06.72,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但那时远远涉及不到这么多钱\N{\fs30}but there was much much less money involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.44,0:30:09.24,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后你进入60年代\N{\fs30}Then as you start to go into the 60's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.24,0:30:11.83,Artifact,,0,0,0,,70年代 从热门专辑到垃圾专辑\N{\fs30}and the 70's, the hit to shit ratio is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.83,0:30:14.01,Artifact,,0,0,0,,分账都是那么低 人们都说:\N{\fs30}so bad that they're saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.01,0:30:16.36,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"嘿 咱不能给当红艺人们钱,"\N{\fs30}"Hey! You know, we can't pay the hit artist
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.36,0:30:18.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"因为还要靠他来养活那些 垃圾的艺人呢"\N{\fs30}cause he is paying for all the bad artists."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.39,0:30:22.35,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这就要说到音乐产业的建立了\N{\fs30}It goes back to how the music industry was set up
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.35,0:30:25.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,在录音行业的起步阶段\N{\fs30}in the very early stages of the recording industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.42,0:30:30.06,Artifact,,0,0,0,,占那些没文化 好糊弄的艺人们的便宜\N{\fs30}taking advantage of uneducated, easily swayed
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.25,0:30:32.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们也不太在乎钱\N{\fs30}artists who don't really care about the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.13,0:30:34.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不幸的是 分道扬镳是常有的事\N{\fs30}Unfortunately there's a lot of fall out with,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.69,0:30:38.10,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还是 乐队薪酬的事 你懂的\N{\fs30}still with bands getting paid, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.10,0:30:39.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们得起诉唱片公司 才能拿到钱\N{\fs30}We had to sue our label to get paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.20,0:30:44.54,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们创造了这样一个奇怪的 错综复杂的系统\N{\fs30}They've created this strange convoluted system
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.59,0:30:47.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,让你得变成个专业律师\N{\fs30}that you have to be a lawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.09,0:30:49.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,才能真正掌握... 或是数学家\N{\fs30}to really understand... Or mathematician.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.24,0:30:52.21,Artifact,,0,0,0,,典型的唱片合约\N{\fs30}A typical record deal is structured
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.21,0:30:53.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,结构是这样的:\N{\fs30}something like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.95,0:30:56.18,Artifact,,0,0,0,,唱片公司付一笔预付款,\N{\fs30}The record label gives an advance say:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.18,0:30:59.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,比如25万美元吧 给艺人录专辑用\N{\fs30}$250.000 to the artist to record an album.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.60,0:31:02.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,艺人于是录了专辑\N{\fs30}The artist then records the album.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.25,0:31:06.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,假设这张专辑买了50万张\N{\fs30}Suppose that the album sales 500.000 copies
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.32,0:31:09.26,Artifact,,0,0,0,,每张10美元 收益是5百万美元\N{\fs30}at $10 each yielding 5 Million Dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.28,0:31:12.02,Artifact,,0,0,0,,唱片公司先把他们的分账\N{\fs30}The record label then takes their cut out
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.02,0:31:15.64,Artifact,,0,0,0,,从五百万里抽出 一般是总销售额的85%\N{\fs30}of the 5 Million, typically 85% of the total sales.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.98,0:31:19.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,给艺人们剩下75万美元\N{\fs30}Leaving the artist with 750.000 dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.41,0:31:22.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但是 在艺人收到钱之前\N{\fs30}But before the artist receives any payments,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.88,0:31:25.20,Artifact,,0,0,0,,公司首先会减去预付款\N{\fs30}the label first deducts the advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.68,0:31:28.21,Artifact,,0,0,0,,此外唱片公司还要扣掉其他费用\N{\fs30}In addition the record label recoups other costs
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.47,0:31:30.23,Artifact,,0,0,0,,例如: 录音费用\N{\fs30}such as: recording costs,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.29,0:31:32.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,一半的推广费用\N{\fs30}half the promotion costs,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.24,0:31:36.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,一半的MV费用 还有巡演资金\N{\fs30}half the video costs, and tour support.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.70,0:31:39.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如此 艺人们还倒欠唱片公司\N{\fs30}This leaves the artist 425.000 Dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.61,0:31:41.22,Artifact,,0,0,0,,42.5万美元\N{\fs30}in debt to the record label.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.77,0:31:43.35,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这项债务流转到\N{\fs30}And then this debt gets carried on
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.35,0:31:44.56,Artifact,,0,0,0,,下张专辑\N{\fs30}to the next album,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.56,0:31:45.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,下下张专辑\N{\fs30}the next album,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.55,0:31:47.18,Artifact,,0,0,0,,再下一张专辑\N{\fs30}and the next album.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.95,0:31:50.47,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我不知道大家有没有看到过\N{\fs30}I don't know if most people have seen
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.48,0:31:52.36,Artifact,,0,0,0,,长期合同 那可真是疯狂\N{\fs30}long form contracts, they're insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.36,0:31:55.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,有那么多的细节 那些细枝末节的东西全都含在里面\N{\fs30}And there's all these little, these little things throwin' in.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.33,0:31:57.06,Artifact,,0,0,0,,跟立法差不多\N{\fs30}It's kind of like legislating,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.06,0:31:58.64,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你懂的 跟为政府制定法律一样\N{\fs30}you know, legislature for a government.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.91,0:32:01.22,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们写上这一大条 但在这条之下\N{\fs30}They put up this big issue\N{\fs30}but underneath that issue
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.22,0:32:04.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,又有比如17条其他的细则\N{\fs30}there's like seventeen other little laws
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.59,0:32:06.69,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们会写进去 但不会告诉你\N{\fs30}that they threw in, that they are not talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.17,0:32:09.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所以 当你同意这一项条款的时候\N{\fs30}So, when you say yes to this one thing
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.07,0:32:10.45,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你其实是在同意\N{\fs30}you are actually saying yes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.45,0:32:11.79,Artifact,,0,0,0,,比如说 45条其他条款\N{\fs30}to like forty-five other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.49,0:32:13.53,Artifact,,0,0,0,,有一条更差的\N{\fs30}There's a worse one,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.53,0:32:16.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们以前还收取网络下载的 损耗费用\N{\fs30}they use to have damage fees with digital downloads.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.33,0:32:17.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,网络下载?\N{\fs30}Digital downloads?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.46,0:32:18.85,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们好像 一开始他们就像是\N{\fs30}Like, at first they were doing that like
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.85,0:32:21.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,犯了谋杀 还想侥幸逃脱一样\N{\fs30}they just trying to get away with murder, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.09,0:32:22.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,像是 "就这么写上吧,"\N{\fs30}It just like "let's leave in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.32,0:32:24.25,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"看他律师能不能看出来" 这样的\N{\fs30}let's see if the lawyer sees it" kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.88,0:32:26.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,合同里的其它的隐藏条款\N{\fs30}Some other hidden items that the contract
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.55,0:32:29.25,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还包括: 包装费\N{\fs30}includes are: packaging costs,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.73,0:32:32.01,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们会在艺人分账里 扣掉上限25%的\N{\fs30}they deduct up to 25% of the artist cut
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.01,0:32:34.54,Artifact,,0,0,0,,名为 为塑料盒和封面图片\N{\fs30}known as the royalty to cover the expense
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.54,0:32:36.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所支付的版税\N{\fs30}of plastic cases and artwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.55,0:32:38.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这项费用甚至在数字下载中也包括\N{\fs30}This cost is even administered to digital downloads
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.80,0:32:42.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而下载的版本是不存在盒子和封面的\N{\fs30}where packaging is non-existent.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.30,0:32:45.72,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还要扣除10%的运输损耗\N{\fs30}10% is deducted to cover breakage costs during shipping.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.72,0:32:47.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,从黑胶唱片的时代就有这些费用\N{\fs30}They started in the vinyl era,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.30,0:32:49.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,到后来CD光盘取代了黑胶唱片\N{\fs30}continued when CDs replaced vinyl
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.46,0:32:52.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如今到了数码下载的年代 这项费用依然存在\N{\fs30}and still applies today with digital downloads.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.14,0:32:55.37,Artifact,,0,0,0,,减除10%的赠送费用 也是一项陈旧环节\N{\fs30}The 10% free goods deduction is an antiquated
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.37,0:32:58.36,Artifact,,0,0,0,,经销商购买100张唱片\N{\fs30}system where retailers purchased 100 albums
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.36,0:33:00.89,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就会另外得到10张免费赠送的\N{\fs30}but are given an additional 10 albums at no charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.52,0:33:03.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而艺人的薪酬只按销售出的唱片来算\N{\fs30}Since the artist is only paid on album sold.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.78,0:33:06.98,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们不会因这些赠品得到补偿\N{\fs30}they are not compensated for those free albums.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.69,0:33:09.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这项扣费 也同样用于\N{\fs30}This deduction still continues
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.58,0:33:12.27,Artifact,,0,0,0,,网络下载为主的市场\N{\fs30}even in a digitally dominated market.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.27,0:33:15.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,艺人们为这么多人 挣来这么多钱\N{\fs30}Artists generate so much money for so many people
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.75,0:33:16.63,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这些人很多都\N{\fs30}that have nothing to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.63,0:33:18.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,与创作过程毫无关联\N{\fs30}the creative process at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.10,0:33:20.69,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你想找一条艺人不被剥削的路\N{\fs30}There is no road you can go down
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.33,0:33:22.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是找不到的\N{\fs30}that the artist isn't fucked.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.27,0:33:24.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,大多数有工作的人们\N{\fs30}Most people out there who have jobs,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.96,0:33:29.52,Artifact,,0,0,0,,都可以去找自己的老板要求加薪\N{\fs30}they can go to their boss ask for a raise,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.09,0:33:31.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们要是实在不满意\N{\fs30}they can leave and go get another job
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.90,0:33:32.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,也可以离开 跳槽\N{\fs30}if they are not happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.15,0:33:35.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而作为音乐人就不能那样\N{\fs30}Musicians don't really have that ability to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.97,0:33:37.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,顺便说一句 "如果我们(唱片公司)不喜欢,\N{\fs30}And by the way, if we don't like,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.04,0:33:38.69,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"如果我们不想再推你的专辑了,\N{\fs30}if we don't feel like pushing your records anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.69,0:33:40.11,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们觉得你不会大卖,\N{\fs30}we don't fell you gonna sell,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.11,0:33:41.87,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"那我们也不会放你们走,\N{\fs30}we're not gonna let you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.87,0:33:44.64,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们只会把你放到一边,\N{\fs30}we're just gonna put you on the shelf over here,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.64,0:33:46.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们不会真正让你做音乐,\N{\fs30}we won't really let you work
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.33,0:33:48.00,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"但也不会让你离开我们公司"\N{\fs30}but we're not gonna let you leave either.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.00,0:33:49.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就像是一桩毫无意义的婚姻\N{\fs30}It's like being in a bad marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.50,0:33:51.31,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你想 要是你丈夫老是打你,\N{\fs30}At what point does your husband beat you up
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.31,0:33:53.57,Artifact,,0,0,0,,或是你妻子总打你 你会说:\N{\fs30}or your wife beat you up and you say:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.57,0:33:55.54,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我受够了 我要走了"\N{\fs30}I had enough I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.54,0:33:57.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,现在就是这么个情况\N{\fs30}That's the point we are at right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.80,0:34:09.62,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我等会儿回来 Irving的电话\N{\fs30}I'll be back in a second, Irving is calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.28,0:34:14.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他跟我说 "这个30秒上火星的事 咱怎么做呢..."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.46,0:34:16.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"因为我们肯定要告到最后的"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.75,0:34:19.51,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后我说  好 我给你解释一下你为什么不能
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.51,0:34:21.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,其他唱片公司会给你们很大压力
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.94,0:34:24.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,相信我 你是新手 我可不是
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.81,0:34:26.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你要上庭 就得当着加州陪审团的面
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.77,0:34:29.95,Artifact,,0,0,0,,与一个签了九年合约 却没拿到一分钱的乐队对质
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.95,0:34:30.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你们会败诉  到那时候...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.99,0:34:33.79,Artifact,,0,0,0,,业内各家唱片公司会做出无数动作
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.79,0:34:36.92,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你们会被业内所有人孤立
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.92,0:34:38.92,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我说 你看 现实是这样的...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.92,0:34:41.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你们花八十亿美元买这个公司
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.46,0:34:43.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,在你们名下 除了酷玩乐队
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.46,0:34:45.10,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们是唯一名副其实的世界级乐队了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.10,0:34:48.18,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不发这张专辑 你们承受不起的
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.18,0:34:49.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,别犯傻了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.05,0:34:53.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你得回去找Guy Hands.  然后他说
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.05,0:34:55.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"那我做不到."  我说 噢那你跟我说...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.14,0:34:57.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,“当事人先生做不到”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.14,0:34:58.82,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那很好啊 没关系啊
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.82,0:35:03.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我说 那你就等着吧 这张专辑很快就会出
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.08,0:35:04.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,知道吗 然后他就说 “我们不会调解的”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.28,0:35:08.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,诉讼已经为我们带来很多负面影响了 媒体压力很大
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.07,0:35:11.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我说 不不不  我们还没开始宣传这官司呢
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.86,0:35:13.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们公司内外 有着亿万个艺人
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.91,0:35:16.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,只有两个乐队与唱片公司有法律纠纷
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.80,0:35:19.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,碎南瓜 和三十秒上火星...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.14,0:35:20.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,都是跟EMI
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.08,0:35:23.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们能阻止我们发布专辑吗?\N{\fs30}Can they stop us from putting a record out?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.07,0:35:38.82,注人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1044,556)}要改变，就要建立新体系，使旧体系失效。\N——理查德·巴克明斯特·富勒\N(著名建筑设计师)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.67,0:35:51.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,真酷啊\N{\fs30}It's really cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.85,0:35:52.95,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这是日本太鼓\N{\fs30}This is Taiko drumming
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.23,0:35:55.35,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我在学习打太鼓\N{\fs30}and I'm learning about Taiko drumming.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.34,0:36:04.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,Shannon演奏起来像个野兽\N{\fs30}Shannon is a beast of a player.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.68,0:36:06.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他不是演奏歌曲\N{\fs30}He doesn't play in a song,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.09,0:36:07.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而是融入其中\N{\fs30}he takes the song over.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.70,0:36:09.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他栖息于之 活在其中\N{\fs30}He inhabits it, he lives it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.14,0:36:09.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,与之同呼吸\N{\fs30}he breathes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.17,0:36:12.17,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他打鼓时散发着一种能量\N{\fs30}There's an energy that he has when he drums
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.17,0:36:14.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,非常震撼 他充满着野性气息\N{\fs30}that's fantastic. He's very animalistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.75,0:36:26.37,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他完全是在情感上共鸣\N{\fs30}He's completely emotionally reacting.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.37,0:36:27.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,看他表演\N{\fs30}It's absolutely fascinating
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.84,0:36:29.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,真是一种视听盛宴\N{\fs30}to watch somebody like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.20,0:36:39.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我哥哥一向热爱音乐\N{\fs30}My brother always had a love of music.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.29,0:36:40.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他真的充满了热情\N{\fs30}He had a real passion for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.47,0:36:46.72,Artifact,,0,0,0,,要不是他 我肯定不会做这个\N{\fs30}I would certainly not be doing this if it wasn't for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.11,0:36:49.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我人生中唯一重视过的 就是音乐\N{\fs30}The only thing I took seriously in my life was music.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.58,0:36:52.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,在三十秒上火星之前\N{\fs30}Before Thirty Seconds to Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.86,0:36:54.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我不知道自己想做什么\N{\fs30}I wasn't sure what I wanted to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.08,0:36:58.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我做过建筑工人 我做过...\N{\fs30}I was doing construction, I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.97,0:37:02.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,违法的事\N{\fs30}Breaking the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.23,0:37:07.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,Jared常常取笑那些误入歧途的孩子\N{\fs30}Jared often jokes about kids from the wrong side of the tracks,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.60,0:37:09.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我绝对就是那种孩子\N{\fs30}I was definitely one of those kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.13,0:37:11.49,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他会消失 你知道\N{\fs30}He would disappear, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.49,0:37:12.52,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他会突然人间蒸发\N{\fs30}he would just disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.94,0:37:15.27,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我从来不知道他在干什么\N{\fs30}I never knew what he was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.30,0:37:19.21,Artifact,,0,0,0,,后来我就遇到了人生的瓶颈\N{\fs30}I reached a point in my life where
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.21,0:37:20.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我需要某种改变\N{\fs30}I needed some sort of change and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.99,0:37:22.83,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而对当时的我来说 音乐是唯一靠谱的\N{\fs30}music was the only thing that made sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.96,0:37:26.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他和Jared开始经常一起演出\N{\fs30}He and Jared started playing together a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.25,0:37:28.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那时我才重视起来\N{\fs30}That's when it got serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.79,0:37:30.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那时我就: "噢! 好吧!\N{\fs30}That's when I was like: "Oh! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.53,0:37:31.68,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我要走这条路了"\N{\fs30}I need to follow this path."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.00,0:37:34.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他才是对做音乐真正充满动力的\N{\fs30}He was the one that was motivated to make music.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.28,0:37:37.51,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他对音乐才是 "要么做 要么死"的\N{\fs30}He was the one that was do or die with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.67,0:37:40.64,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们一起演奏时散发出的能量\N{\fs30}Just the energy of us playing together.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.93,0:37:41.79,Artifact,,0,0,0,,真让人兴奋\N{\fs30}That was exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.19,0:37:45.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我只想演奏 演奏 演奏 演奏\N{\fs30}I just wanted to play, play, play, play.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.10,0:38:08.74,Artifact,,0,0,0,,好了 秘密据点 拉钩保密?!\N{\fs30}Okay. Secret spot. Pinky swear?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.25,0:38:11.79,Artifact,,0,0,0,,反正我也找不到 所以不用担心\N{\fs30}I'll never be able to find it anyway. So, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.74,0:38:15.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,好 到底啥事?\N{\fs30}So, what's the deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.28,0:38:16.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,过两天你要去开个很久的会\N{\fs30}You had a long meeting the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.16,0:38:19.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,嗯 EMI想要达成个协议\N{\fs30}Yeah, EMI wants to make a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.37,0:38:21.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,有意思\N{\fs30}Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.86,0:38:24.69,Artifact,,0,0,0,,虽然是个渣协议 但总是个协议\N{\fs30}It's a shitty deal but, it's a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.61,0:38:28.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那么 咱们有两种选择\N{\fs30}So, we have a couple of options.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.53,0:38:33.37,Artifact,,0,0,0,,一种是激动人心的: 我们自立门户\N{\fs30}There's the option that's exciting to go on our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.69,0:38:36.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,感觉有了这样的独立精神,\N{\fs30}It feels like there's a lot of opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.03,0:38:41.52,Artifact,,0,0,0,,机会就会像潮水般涌来 只要有这种心态...\N{\fs30}with that independent spirit and taking the mindset at...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.32,0:38:46.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不跟那个 不作为的公司签\N{\fs30}Rather than signing an antiquated deal with a company
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.94,0:38:52.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,过时很久的老套合约\N{\fs30}that has no interest in really doing anything
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.91,0:38:54.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们眼里只有钱\N{\fs30}except making the numbers work.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.95,0:38:56.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但那是现实\N{\fs30}But that's the reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.61,0:38:58.54,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如果你想签个唱片合同\N{\fs30}if you want to sign a record deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.10,0:39:00.65,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你就得那样\N{\fs30}That's what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.65,0:39:02.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,居高临下 两手准备\N{\fs30}High nose. Both options.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.89,0:39:04.67,Artifact,,0,0,0,,Jared?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.25,0:39:07.51,Artifact,,0,0,0,,两手准备可都是要赌很大的\N{\fs30}Both options are a big gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.70,0:39:10.20,Artifact,,0,0,0,,嗯 我知道的不太多 所以没主意\N{\fs30}Yeah, I don't know enough to have a real opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.20,0:39:11.74,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但看起来 好像咱们自立门户\N{\fs30}But it's seems like going on our own
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.74,0:39:12.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是唯一的选择了\N{\fs30}is the only way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.26,0:39:14.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我不知道 这很难\N{\fs30}I don't know, it's hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.05,0:39:15.39,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你给我说一个 不签任何唱片公司\N{\fs30}Give me a name of one band
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.39,0:39:17.18,Artifact,,0,0,0,,却取得了全球范围成功\N{\fs30}that's had continued worldwide success
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.18,0:39:18.43,Artifact,,0,0,0,,的乐队名字\N{\fs30}without a label.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.02,0:39:21.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我说不出来\N{\fs30}I can't give you one.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.10,0:39:24.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,有人说 就签约吧\N{\fs30}Some people say to take the deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.34,0:39:25.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,完事\N{\fs30}Settle.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.72,0:39:30.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,嗯... 能签就签\N{\fs30}Yeah... Just take whatever deal you can get
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.72,0:39:32.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,现在的形势这么混乱\N{\fs30}cause this is so fucked right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.20,0:39:37.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,基本上 你找唱片公司\N{\fs30}Basically, you're looking for a record company
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.69,0:39:40.41,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就是处理各种具体事务用的\N{\fs30}to handle very specific things
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.41,0:39:42.53,Artifact,,0,0,0,,比如推广 营销 以及其他的\N{\fs30}like promotion, marketing, and things
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.53,0:39:44.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我自己一点也不想做的事\N{\fs30}that I don't really want to have to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.52,0:39:45.77,Artifact,,0,0,0,,对\N{\fs30}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.77,0:39:50.43,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如果咱们完全独立 我就得...\N{\fs30}If we go completely independent, I'll end up...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.92,0:39:54.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,把全部生活都投入进去  早晨 中午 晚上\N{\fs30}That will be my life - morning, noon and night
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.14,0:39:57.13,Artifact,,0,0,0,,都得用来做唱片公司做的 所有事\N{\fs30}- is going to be having to have a record company.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.34,0:39:59.67,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你想玩"进击"吗\N{\fs30}You feel you want to push army.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.01,0:40:02.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,嗯 我想玩"进击"\N{\fs30}Yeah, I want to push army.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.33,0:40:04.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你自己选一块石头\N{\fs30}You take the rock of your choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.18,0:40:08.85,Artifact,,0,0,0,,或是别的大块东西 看你心里有多大的事了\N{\fs30}or a bolder depending how big your issue is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.95,0:40:12.20,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后你把它扔过山崖\N{\fs30}And you throw it over the precipice
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.20,0:40:14.57,Artifact,,0,0,0,,扔的时候 你要大叫\N{\fs30}and when you throw it, you scream,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.57,0:40:17.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,释放出你生活中\N{\fs30}and you let go of this particular aspect of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.84,0:40:20.76,Artifact,,0,0,0,,内心的特殊情绪 或是困扰你的事情\N{\fs30}who you are or something in your life that's plaguing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.76,0:40:23.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后你就把它抛之脑后 然后...\N{\fs30}And you leave it behind and...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.60,0:40:27.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后 嗯 这就是咱现在要做的\N{\fs30}And, well, we gonna do it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.40,0:40:28.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我先来还是你先来?\N{\fs30}I'm gonna start or you wanna?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.50,0:40:29.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我先来吧\N{\fs30}I go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.40,0:40:30.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,嗯 你先\N{\fs30}Yeah, you go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.93,0:40:32.89,Artifact,,0,0,0,,看你有多大能耐\N{\fs30}Let's see what you got.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.53,0:40:43.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我听见有人叫 "哎呦!"\N{\fs30}I just heard somebody say "ouch!"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.61,0:40:56.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不错诶\N{\fs30}That's pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.34,0:40:59.36,Artifact,,0,0,0,,没有落地吗 发生了什么...\N{\fs30}It never landed... what's that been...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.66,0:41:02.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,真特么变态\N{\fs30}This is so fucking nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.90,0:41:03.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\fs30}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.05,0:41:05.52,Artifact,,0,0,0,,对了 我想出\N{\fs30}By the way, I think I came up
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.52,0:41:06.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,新专辑的名字了\N{\fs30}with a name for the album.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.61,0:41:08.12,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是什么?\N{\fs30}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.87,0:41:09.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,<全面开战>\N{\fs30}"This is War."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.98,0:41:14.71,Artifact,,0,0,0,,现在做音乐 录歌 比以前容易多了\N{\fs30}It's easier than ever to make music and record it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.18,0:41:16.57,Artifact,,0,0,0,,拍MV并录制好\N{\fs30}It's easier than ever to make videos
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.57,0:41:17.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,也容易的多\N{\fs30}and record them properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.04,0:41:19.87,Artifact,,0,0,0,,把它们发布出来也很容易\N{\fs30}It's easier than ever to put them out there
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.19,0:41:22.52,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但是要使它们被听到 却是前所未有的难\N{\fs30}but it's harder than ever to make them heard
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.87,0:41:24.66,Artifact,,0,0,0,,得到点击量很难 因为网络上有太多声音\N{\fs30}or have them heard because there's so much noise
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.66,0:41:26.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所以唱片公司\N{\fs30}on the internet so a record company
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.88,0:41:29.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,仍要承担起 帮助筛选这些\N{\fs30}still has to do the job of helping to filter that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.81,0:41:31.89,Artifact,,0,0,0,,并加以适当宣传\N{\fs30}and to promote things properly
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.89,0:41:33.27,Artifact,,0,0,0,,让歌曲受到关注的工作\N{\fs30}so that they can get noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.84,0:41:35.49,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而且不用唱片公司 也能很成功的艺人\N{\fs30}And there's certainly exceptions of artists
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.49,0:41:37.44,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这样的例外显然也是有的\N{\fs30}that have done well without a record company
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.44,0:41:42.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但是大多数来讲 广大的艺人群体\N{\fs30}but by in large the overwhelming majority of artists
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.14,0:41:44.02,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那些功成名就 你懂的\N{\fs30}that have achieved, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.02,0:41:45.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,取得了大范围成功的艺人 都是签了大厂牌的\N{\fs30}major success, have been signed to major labels.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.31,0:41:48.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,大厂牌 都是Cyclopes独眼巨人\N{\fs30}Major labels are giant Cyclopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.94,0:41:50.90,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(68,582)}OK Go乐队主唱
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.55,0:41:51.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们有一只怪物般的能量强大的巨眼\N{\fs30}and they have one very monstrously powerful eye
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.19,0:41:52.48,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就在他们额头正中\N{\fs30}right in the middle of their forehead
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.48,0:41:54.36,Artifact,,0,0,0,,当它看向你时 你懂的\N{\fs30}and when it's staring at you, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.36,0:41:55.63,Artifact,,0,0,0,,全世界都明亮发光\N{\fs30}the world is a very bright and shiny place.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.63,0:41:58.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而它不看你时 你就得不到任何关注\N{\fs30}And when it's not, there is no getting attention of that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.05,0:42:00.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如果我认识的某乐队要签个大厂牌\N{\fs30}If I knew a band was going to sign a major label deal,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.28,0:42:02.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我一定会尽力劝阻他们\N{\fs30}I would probably try to dissuade them
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.40,0:42:04.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,或者至少也要问清\N{\fs30}or I would at least try to figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.16,0:42:06.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们以为自己能从中得到什么\N{\fs30}what they thought they were gonna get out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.14,0:42:10.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如今唱片公司越来越少地\N{\fs30}Increasingly, artist development is a term
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.29,0:42:13.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,使用"艺人发展"这个词了 你懂的\N{\fs30}that's not even used at record companies, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.82,0:42:15.20,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们偶尔也提"艺人发展"\N{\fs30}They use the word artist development
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.20,0:42:16.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但这一般是个禁忌话题\N{\fs30}but it's offensive to a certain point
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.38,0:42:17.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,因为他们才不管什么"艺人发展"\N{\fs30}cause they don't really do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.60,0:42:18.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们找数据\N{\fs30}They look at the profiles,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.94,0:42:20.73,Artifact,,0,0,0,,过去是在MySpace上找\N{\fs30}in the old days, it was MySpace,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.73,0:42:23.18,Artifact,,0,0,0,,现在是在Facebook, YouTube, Twitter上\N{\fs30}the profile numbers now it's Facebook,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.18,0:42:24.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,找数据资料\N{\fs30}YouTube, Twitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.14,0:42:27.21,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不用唱片公司 你能独立卖掉1万 2万张专辑吗\N{\fs30}Can you sell 10 / 20 000 on your own without a label
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.21,0:42:30.22,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如果能 他们就该关注你了\N{\fs30}and if so, then they start paying attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.22,0:42:32.08,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你懂的 只是比较关注 嗯\N{\fs30}you know, kind of thing, but yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.08,0:42:33.04,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但也不是关注艺人的发展\N{\fs30}but it's not artist development.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.04,0:42:35.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那签的都是自己已经颇有成就的艺人\N{\fs30}That's already signing an artist that's developed itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.29,0:42:37.64,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我想现在人们签约唱片公司 真正原因是\N{\fs30}I think the main reason people really want labels now
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.64,0:42:40.54,Artifact,,0,0,0,,正规性 尤其当你是个新人乐队\N{\fs30}it's legitimacy, especially when you are a new band that,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.54,0:42:44.18,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你所作的选择真的事关重大\N{\fs30}that what you're doing really kind of matters
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.18,0:42:45.69,Artifact,,0,0,0,,受到媒体的曝光 真的很重要\N{\fs30}and is part of something, and to get the press,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.69,0:42:47.17,Artifact,,0,0,0,,让人们逐渐认同你\N{\fs30}to get people believing in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.17,0:42:48.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所以显然 当乐队自身影响变大之后\N{\fs30}So obviously, bands when they get big on their own
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.97,0:42:51.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们签唱片公司就是为了: 正规性\N{\fs30}then they sign with a label for that: Legitimacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.42,0:42:54.34,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(816,580)}Topspin传媒公司 首席执行官
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.56,0:42:52.89,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们学到的一点就是\N{\fs30}One thing we've definitely learn
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.89,0:42:54.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,艺人们需要协助\N{\fs30}is that artists need help.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.34,0:43:01.35,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(872,254)}摇滚乐队宣布独立
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.94,0:42:56.57,Artifact,,0,0,0,,公制乐队就是个好例子\N{\fs30}Metric is a great example.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.57,0:42:58.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们是第一个 进入电台流行榜单前五位的\N{\fs30}They were the first artists to break top 5
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.58,0:43:00.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,独立艺人团体\N{\fs30}in pop radio with no label.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.95,0:43:03.43,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但如果你跟他们的经理人Matt Drouin聊\N{\fs30}But if you talked to Matt Drouin
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.43,0:43:05.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他就会告诉你:\N{\fs30}who manages Metric, he will tell you:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.16,0:43:07.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们雇来制作专辑的人\N{\fs30}"We had more people working on that record
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.61,0:43:09.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"比在唱片公司时还要多\N{\fs30}than if we were at a label.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.33,0:43:11.32,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们只是自己雇他们而已 所以 没错\N{\fs30}We just hired them ourselves so, no,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.32,0:43:12.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们是没有签厂牌\N{\fs30}we didn't have a label but
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.50,0:43:14.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们差不多是自己建立了整套的员工系统"\N{\fs30}we kind of built our own staff around it."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.36,0:43:19.45,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(394,384)}阿曼达·帕尔默对RoadRunner唱片公司说：\N请甩我
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.60,0:43:18.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我离开唱片公司时 基本就知道\N{\fs30}When I got off the label, I pretty much knew
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.46,0:43:20.11,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我不想再签一家\N{\fs30}I didn't want to sign with another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.11,0:43:22.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我知道 没有什么比自己直接与我的粉丝交易更好的了\N{\fs30}And I knew nothing could beat doing direct business
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.87,0:43:24.66,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1120,698)}音乐人
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.30,0:43:23.97,Artifact,,0,0,0,,并不是...\N{\fs30}with my fans, it wasn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.57,0:43:26.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,世界上任何合约也比不上这样\N{\fs30}There was no deal in the world that was that good.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.78,0:43:28.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我都数不清自己收到了多少邮件\N{\fs30}I cannot tell you how many eMails
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.91,0:43:31.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,粉丝们纷纷跟我说:\N{\fs30}I've got from fans saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.86,0:43:33.56,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们想直接支持你,\N{\fs30}"We want to directly support you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.56,0:43:36.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我们该怎么做 才能不让钱跑到唱片公司手上?"\N{\fs30}How can we do it so your label doesn't get the money?"
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.19,0:43:43.31,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(842,216)}阿曼达·帕尔默谈论\N其百万美元启动项目\N“音乐的未来”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.42,0:43:40.26,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你给人们提供超赞的音乐\N{\fs30}Give people awesome music
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.26,0:43:42.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们就会很乐意帮助你\N{\fs30}and then make it very easy for them to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.78,0:43:44.42,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而且他们真的会\N{\fs30}And they will.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.93,0:43:49.94,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(858,526)}Chester French乐队主唱\N "声破天"音乐软件驻唱艺人
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.42,0:43:46.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我之前说过 有好多艺人\N{\fs30}There are lots of artists, like I said
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.38,0:43:49.39,Artifact,,0,0,0,,都面临着这个这个选择\N{\fs30}who were finding themselves with this choice
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.39,0:43:50.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,并不是说\N{\fs30}and it is not to say
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.78,0:43:53.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,唱片公司不会赢得诉讼\N{\fs30}that the labels can't win the argument
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.16,0:43:55.94,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而是说艺人该如何利用唱片公司\N{\fs30}as to why an artist should use them
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.94,0:43:58.72,Artifact,,0,0,0,,与他们合作 呃... 不过确实\N{\fs30}and partner with them. Em... But it is to say
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.72,0:44:02.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还有很多种途径可以选择\N{\fs30}that there is a great number of tools available
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.81,0:44:05.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,让独立艺人们可以自行制作\N{\fs30}to independent artists to do it on their own
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.58,0:44:07.87,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这样做出来 也不一定会\N{\fs30}and they are not necessarily considerably
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.87,0:44:10.74,Artifact,,0,0,0,,比唱片公司做的差\N{\fs30}inferior to the label choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.52,0:44:26.36,Artifact,,0,0,0,,节拍数是多少?\N{\fs30}What's the BPM?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.01,0:44:29.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,开!\N{\fs30}GO!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.35,0:44:48.12,Artifact,,0,0,0,,下一段副歌\N{\fs30}Next chorus!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.12,0:44:49.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,感谢大家 祝您丫的今日愉快!\N{\fs30}Thank you very much, have a nice fucking day!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.33,0:44:59.23,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我那时21岁 只要能以音乐为生\N{\fs30}I was 21 years old and I would do anything
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.70,0:45:02.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,让我干什么都行\N{\fs30}in order to be able to play music for a living.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.13,0:45:05.26,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但我已经下定决心要放弃了\N{\fs30}But I had made the choice to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.68,0:45:07.69,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我意识到已经错过了机会\N{\fs30}I realized I had missed my boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.16,0:45:10.56,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我已经计划好 要卖掉我所有的设备\N{\fs30}I had made plans to sell all of my gear,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.60,0:45:15.51,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我不想 留下任何关于音乐生涯的记忆\N{\fs30}I didn't want to have any like, memory of the music life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.51,0:45:18.72,Artifact,,0,0,0,,第二天 大概是在我下定决心后\N{\fs30}The next day, after like, making this choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.11,0:45:20.90,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我就接到了电话\N{\fs30}is when I got the call to see if
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.90,0:45:22.57,Artifact,,0,0,0,,问我想不想来面试\N{\fs30}I was interested in auditioning
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.57,0:45:23.85,Artifact,,0,0,0,,加入三十秒上火星\N{\fs30}for Thirty Seconds to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.75,0:45:26.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我那时几乎完全破产 一点钱没有\N{\fs30}I'm like completely broke. I have no money,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.88,0:45:28.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,什么都没有 我只有一把吉他\N{\fs30}I have nothing at all. I have a guitar
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.07,0:45:31.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还有点破设备 我求着我爸妈\N{\fs30}and some crappy gear. And I begged my parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.58,0:45:33.13,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我说 就是这次了 我能感觉到\N{\fs30}I was like, this is the one, I can feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.13,0:45:34.89,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我知道 我能拿到它\N{\fs30}I know, I'm gonna get this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.89,0:45:36.66,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不论怎样 什么都不能阻止我入选\N{\fs30}No matter what, nothing gonna stop me from getting this,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.66,0:45:38.19,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如果我没通过 我会死的\N{\fs30}I will die if I don't get this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.59,0:45:40.46,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们当时面试了大概有几百人\N{\fs30}We're auditioning like hundreds of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.79,0:45:41.73,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他走进来就说:\N{\fs30}He walks in and he says:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.73,0:45:44.20,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"我来就是告诉你们,\N{\fs30}"I just want to let you guys know
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.20,0:45:45.65,Artifact,,0,0,0,,"你们不用再找别人了..."\N{\fs30}you don't have to look any further..."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.65,0:45:47.69,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我当时那么狂妄 那么蠢\N{\fs30}I was so cocky and so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.69,0:45:50.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我表现成那样 完全有可能把一切都搞砸\N{\fs30}It could have gone so badly, the way I was acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.07,0:45:54.49,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我就说：好啊 嗯 那咱看看吧\N{\fs30}I was like, alright, well, see what you got.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.17,0:45:56.37,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们把机会给了我\N{\fs30}They took a chance on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.65,0:45:58.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我不是长得最漂亮的孩子\N{\fs30}I wasn't the coolest looking kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.33,0:46:01.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我肯定也不是那里最棒的吉他手\N{\fs30}I certainly wasn't the best guitarist out there
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.30,0:46:04.11,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但显然我身上有某种东西 被他们看中了\N{\fs30}but there was obviously something that they saw in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.90,0:46:38.90,地名,,0,0,0,,诉讼第75天
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.06,0:46:51.18,Artifact,,0,0,0,,与EMI重订合约 摆脱二百万美元的债务\N{\fs30}Re-signing with EMI, gets rid of 2 Million Dollars of all debt
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.66,0:46:55.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,也摆脱3000万美元的官司\N{\fs30}and gets rid of the Thirty Million Dollars lawsuit
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.30,0:46:58.24,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但那真他妈气人啊 这样解决   -我知道\N{\fs30}but that fucking pissing me, this won,    -I know
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.99,0:47:00.12,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这甚至不是打架的那种\N{\fs30}and it's not even the fight
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.12,0:47:02.11,Artifact,,0,0,0,,可以打倒某人的斗争\N{\fs30}to fight to beat somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.11,0:47:06.54,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这场斗争是为了 为了正义 为了公平!\N{\fs30}It's the fight to... to... for what's right, what's fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.54,0:47:09.16,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你妥协一些 签下合约\N{\fs30}You sign a deal in a way to compromise
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.55,0:47:10.67,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但你这样做是为了\N{\fs30}but you're doing it so that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.87,0:47:14.24,Artifact,,0,0,0,,可以打入内部\N{\fs30}you could get in on the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.24,0:47:15.65,Artifact,,0,0,0,,与对方合作\N{\fs30}work with somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.65,0:47:17.63,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后改变现有模式的基础\N{\fs30}and change the fundamentals
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.63,0:47:18.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而不是用对抗的方式解决\N{\fs30}that way rather than a confrontation.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.61,0:47:20.27,Artifact,,0,0,0,,是啊 从内部改变它\N{\fs30}Yeah, changing from the inside out.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.27,0:47:21.13,Artifact,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\fs30}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.13,0:47:24.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,或是 可不可以从外部对抗它?\N{\fs30}Or do you confront it from the outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.09,0:47:26.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我们再也不会有这样的机会了\N{\fs30}We would never have this opportunity again
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.70,0:47:28.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,用7年条款来打官司\N{\fs30}to fight over the 7-year clause
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.59,0:47:31.78,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后努力做到 改变一点(这个体系)\N{\fs30}and to go and like, change a part of...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.78,0:47:32.34,Artifact,,0,0,0,,完全如此\N{\fs30}Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.84,0:47:34.86,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不仅是改变音乐行业\N{\fs30}Not just the music business
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.86,0:47:39.02,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还有我们的合约的签订方式\N{\fs30}but you know, the way that our contracts are handled.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.02,0:47:41.31,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所以有一种... 你懂的\N{\fs30}So there is this kind of... You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.21,0:47:43.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,...道德讨伐\N{\fs30}... Moral crusade.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.73,0:47:45.95,Artifact,,0,0,0,,对 是有点道德讨伐的意思\N{\fs30}Yeah, there's a bit of a moral crusade.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.95,0:47:48.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,如果他们把我们想要的一切\N{\fs30}If they give us every single fucking thing
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.33,0:47:51.33,Artifact,,0,0,0,,都他妈给我们\N{\fs30}that we wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.33,0:47:52.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们还是赚着大头啊\N{\fs30}they would still be winning
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.61,0:47:53.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而且他们也知道\N{\fs30}and they know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.88,0:47:56.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,重点就是这个 他们他妈的知道!\N{\fs30}That's the thing they're fuckin' know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.59,0:47:59.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,而且 妈的 他们在乎个屁\N{\fs30}And by the way, what the Fuck! What do they give a shit,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.85,0:48:02.49,Artifact,,0,0,0,,每天下班 他们总能回到家 拿着工资\N{\fs30}they gonna go home and get their salary at the end of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.49,0:48:04.51,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们要什么有什么\N{\fs30}They're getting everything that they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.51,0:48:08.38,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们有对艺人的完全控制权\N{\fs30}Complete domination over the artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.38,0:48:10.10,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你要小心点 迷恋...\N{\fs30}Just be careful you know, addict...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.10,0:48:13.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,说迷恋可能太重了... 身在这个位置\N{\fs30}Addicted is a strong word, to be the person
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.55,0:48:15.41,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就总要面对斗争的\N{\fs30}that is always gonna be in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.69,0:48:19.91,Artifact,,0,0,0,,可能 现在并不是斗争的最佳时机\N{\fs30}Maybe this is not the right time to fight this
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.31,0:48:24.17,Artifact,,0,0,0,,不要抗争这个体制 先等待一阵\N{\fs30}through this mechanism. Just bide your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.17,0:48:27.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,用另一种方式来抗争 可能更好\N{\fs30}It might well be a different way to fight it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.58,0:48:29.69,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那样你就不用牺牲那么大\N{\fs30}But you don't have to sacrifice as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.96,0:48:35.40,Artifact,,0,0,0,,唱片公司 总是比艺人更持久\N{\fs30}The Company can always outlast the act.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.61,0:48:38.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这一点我们是从乔治·迈克尔的案子学到的\N{\fs30}We learn this lesson primarily with Georges Michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.41,0:48:40.53,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他因为状告索尼 结束了他的职业生涯 是吧\N{\fs30}He killed his career suing Sony, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.01,0:48:42.99,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所以艺人总是先提出调解\N{\fs30}So, the act has an incentive to settle
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.99,0:48:45.41,Artifact,,0,0,0,,因为艺人们可不像IBM的工程师\N{\fs30}because acts are not like engineers at IBM
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.41,0:48:47.55,Artifact,,0,0,0,,可以工作上40年\N{\fs30}who might work for 40 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.53,0:48:51.78,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(342,558)}披头士乐队状告EMI 要求赔偿数百万
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.78,0:48:55.91,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(400,378)}金属乐队状告唱片公司 援引"7年"合同条例
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.91,0:49:01.46,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(208,248)}Prince退出录音 转向其他行业
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.90,0:48:59.23,Artifact,,0,0,0,,当年Prince被华纳公司气坏了\N{\fs30}Prince was pissed off at Warner Brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.46,0:49:07.71,注释,,0,0,0,,(注：1993年 华纳兄弟公司旗下艺人Prince将名字改成了\N无法发音的"O(+>", 直到2000年与华纳解约后才改回来)
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.23,0:49:01.59,Artifact,,0,0,0,,于是停止了录音 就是那时\N{\fs30}and stopped recording that's when
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.59,0:49:04.03,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他把名字改成了那个符号\N{\fs30}he changed his name to that symbol.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.03,0:49:07.66,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那是对华纳兄弟的反抗\N{\fs30}It was a protest against Warner Brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.66,0:49:09.22,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那怎么做才是正确的呢?\N{\fs30}So, was that the right thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.97,0:49:13.75,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你知道 像他那样高度的人 去坐冷板凳\N{\fs30}You know, at the kind of his height, to go sit on the sidelines
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.75,0:49:16.00,Artifact,,0,0,0,,然后过了很多很多年之后才重新回来做音乐\N{\fs30}and then go make music how many every years later
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.00,0:49:18.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,到那时谁还想为这个打官司?\N{\fs30}when people don't want to fight about it anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.62,0:49:22.09,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我不知道 谁输谁赢?\N{\fs30}I don't know. Who won? Who lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.90,0:49:27.94,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(602,454)}林肯公园乐队想要解约
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.08,0:49:27.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我只记到那时一直想:\N{\fs30}I just remember the whole time thinking:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.81,0:49:32.60,Artifact,,0,0,0,,跟唱片公司相互斗气\N{\fs30}It's not a good idea to go into a pissing contest
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.60,0:49:34.17,Artifact,,0,0,0,,可不是什么好主意\N{\fs30}with the record company,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.32,0:49:37.28,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们有 他们拿着所有的牌\N{\fs30}who has, who holds all the cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.62,0:49:38.88,Artifact,,0,0,0,,这就是场消耗战\N{\fs30}It's like a war of attrition.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.88,0:49:42.47,Artifact,,0,0,0,,像是 谁先把对方耗垮了\N{\fs30}It's like, whoever wears the other person down first
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.47,0:49:43.61,Artifact,,0,0,0,,谁就赢\N{\fs30}is going to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.92,0:49:46.04,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(370,566)}大西洋唱片状告Stone Temple Pilots乐队\N的Weiland(主唱)和Kretz(鼓手)
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.04,0:49:48.09,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(700,496)}碎南瓜乐队状告维珍唱片
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.09,0:49:50.09,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(450,566)}平克·弗洛伊德乐队\N因版税问题状告EMI
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.46,0:49:53.23,Artifact,,0,0,0,,一般 唱片公司想给艺人们点教训\N{\fs30}Usually the company they want to teach the act a lesson,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.23,0:49:54.96,Artifact,,0,0,0,,但是也需要艺人给他们挣钱\N{\fs30}but they also need the revenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.73,0:49:57.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所以 假设艺人愿意在冷板凳上\N{\fs30}So, assuming the act is willing to sit
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.50,0:49:59.14,Artifact,,0,0,0,,坐上个一两年\N{\fs30}on the sidelines for a year or two,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.14,0:50:00.85,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们最后绝对能签个好点的合约\N{\fs30}they can ultimately make a better deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.06,0:50:03.11,Artifact,,0,0,0,,只是但愿他们不会在这期间失去势头\N{\fs30}Hopefully they've not lost momentum in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.89,0:50:09.07,网页,,0,0,0,,{\pos(704,396)}OK Go乐队与EMI分手
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.58,0:50:09.41,Artifact,,0,0,0,,你觉得EMI 作为大公司\N{\fs30}Do you think as a corporation EMI
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.69,0:50:14.32,注次级人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(66,582)}OK Go乐队主唱
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.41,0:50:10.30,Artifact,,0,0,0,,有没有骗过你?\N{\fs30}ever lied to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.22,0:50:13.72,Artifact,,0,0,0,,呃...我觉得EMI有没有骗过我们?\N{\fs30}Erm... Do I think EMI ever lied to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.11,0:50:15.17,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我...\N{\fs30}I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.58,0:50:18.58,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我在想怎么说才不用赔3000万块钱\N{\fs30}I'm seeking not to get sued by 30 Million bucks,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.58,0:50:20.50,Artifact,,0,0,0,,好 我不告诉你他们是怎样的\N{\fs30}So, I can't tell you or not how they are inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.12,0:50:22.80,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我是说 这是我们和解的唯一条件\N{\fs30}I mean that's the only condition of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.80,0:50:24.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,就是我要乖乖听话\N{\fs30}our release that I got to be a good boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.06,0:50:32.17,Artifact,,0,0,0,,那 给我点专业意见吧 朋友\N{\fs30}So, give me some counsel here, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.17,0:50:33.05,Artifact,,0,0,0,,我要做什么?\N{\fs30}What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.39,0:50:36.81,Artifact,,0,0,0,,咱先说明白 他们是一帮让律师洗了脑的白痴
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.40,0:50:41.07,注人名,,0,0,0,,{\pos(440,131)}乐队律师
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.81,0:50:41.07,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们认为自己被逼上了绝路 打碎了牙往肚子里咽
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.07,0:50:44.70,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们现在的三观就是这样的 不管是对是错吧
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.70,0:50:49.29,Artifact,,0,0,0,,所以每次我跟他们说点什么 都像是在他们肚子里又深入了一厘米
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.29,0:50:51.95,Artifact,,0,0,0,,他们就是这样看待世界的
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.08,0:50:54.71,Artifact,,0,0,0,,还有再说一次 我不是说同意或赞成他们
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.71,0:50:57.84,Artifact,,0,0,0,,只是把情况告诉你 知己知彼是很重要的
